e Department has a database of voices of suspects. You are appointed to help them and find out the thief. </span></span></span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal">\r\n	<span style="font-size: 12px;"><span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;"><span lang="EN-US" style="line-height: 115%;">Tools at your disposal:</span></span></span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal">\r\n	<strong><span style="font-size: 12px;"><span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;"><span lang="EN-US" style="line-height: 115%;">Matlab<br />\r\n	</span></span></span></strong></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;"><strong>Round 3</strong></span></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Details of Round 3 to be revealed on the spot.</p>\r\n', 'signalytics', '4af9dcf3-b600-4454-8326-1064bb1aea99', '<p>\r\n	<strong>Rules:<br />\r\n	</strong></p>\r\n<div style="background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); font-family: arial,verdana,sans-serif; color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-size: 12px;">\r\n	<div>\r\n		<span _fck_bookmark="1" id="cke_bm_591E" style="display: none;">&nbsp;</span>\r\n		<ol>\r\n			<li>\r\n				<p>\r\n					A team has to participate in the online round.</p>\r\n			</li>\r\n			<li>\r\n				<p>\r\n					The top teams from Online Phase 1 will be automatically selected for the On-Campus Rounds.</p>\r\n			</li>\r\n			<li>\r\n				<p>\r\n					<span style="font-size: 12px;"><span lang="EN-US" style="line-height: 115%;">Followed by on-campus Round 2 ,there will be a &lsquo;VIVA&rsquo; session where participants will have to explain their algorithm</span></span></p>\r\n				<p>\r\n					<span style="font-size: 12px;"><strong>Certification:</strong></span></p>\r\n			</li>\r\n		</ol>\r\n	</div>\r\n	<ol>\r\n		<li>\r\n			Certificate of Merit will be given to the top three contestants.</li>\r\n		<li>\r\n			Certificates of Participation will be given to all the teams who qualify for the final round.</li>\r\n	</ol>\r\n</div>\r\n', '<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<span _fck_bookmark="1" id="cke_bm_588S" style="display: none;">&nbsp;</span>Final score will be a sum of marks of all three rounds.&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		In case of a tie, time factor will be considered.</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<p class="MsoNormal">\r\n			<span style="font-size: 12px;"><span lang="EN-US" style="line-height: 115%;">Problem can be solved by using any algorithm.</span></span></p>\r\n		<p class="MsoNormal">\r\n			<span style="font-size: 14px;"><span lang="EN-US" style="line-height: 115%; font-family: &quot;Calibri&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;">Problem will be divided into modules. Each module has to be solved and points will be awarded accordingly.<br />\r\n			</span></span></p>\r\n		<p class="MsoNormal">\r\n			Decisions made by the S.P.A.M team will be final in case of any discrepancy.&nbsp;<span _fck_bookmark="1" id="cke_bm_588E" style="display: none;">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<strong>Eligibility:</strong></p>\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n		All students with a valid identity card of their respective educational institutes are eligible to participate in the event.</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Participants are expected to have basic knowledge of MATLAB.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n', '<div>\r\n	<div>\r\n		<b>Resources are now up!!!!!<br />\r\n		</b></div>\r\n	<div>\r\n		<a href="http://www.bits-quark.org/portal//files/word_recognition.pdf">http://www.bits-quark.org/portal//files/word_recognition.pdf<br />\r\n		</a></div>\r\n	<div>\r\n		&nbsp;</div>\r\n	<div>\r\n		<strong>Algorithm for ROUND 1<br />\r\n		</strong></div>\r\n	<div>\r\n		<a href="http://www.bits-quark.org/portal/files/spam_resource.pdf">http://www.bits-quark.org/portal/files/spam_resource.pdf<br />\r\n		</a></div>\r\n	<div>\r\n		&nbsp;</div>\r\n	<div>\r\n		You can check these links for Round1 :</div>\r\n	<div>\r\n		&nbsp;</div>\r\n	<div>\r\n		http://www.libinst.com/cepst.htm</div>\r\n	<div>\r\n		&nbsp;</div>\r\n	<div>\r\n		http://www.emt.uni-linz.ac.at/education/Inhalte/se_moderne_methoden/WS0304/Gessl-Cepstrum.pdf</div>\r\n</div>\r\n', '<div>\r\n	If you have any query, please send an e-mail to <strong><br />\r\n	spam@bits-quark.org</strong>, or get in touch with any one of us:</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	<strong>Karan Bohra</strong></div>\r\n<div>\r\n	+91 9860745142</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	<strong>Nikita Bharadia</strong></div>\r\n<div>\r\n	+91 7709790812</div>\r\n', 1, 3);
INSERT INTO `events` (`id`, `name`, `intro`, `details`, `route`, `category_id`, `rules`, `judging_criteria`, `additional_info`, `contact`, `min_participants`, `max_participants`) VALUES
('4cbc72ea-bd14-4b0b-a222-05d80a030849', 'Burnout', '<p>\r\n	<span style="font-size: 16px;"><strong><span style="font-size: 12px;">Presented By</span><br />\r\n	&nbsp;<a href="http://www.mahindrascorpio.com/home.aspx" target="_blank"><img alt="Scorpio" height="212" src="http://www.bits-quark.org/portal/img/uploads/BE-Logo1.jpg" width="150" /></a></strong></span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: right;">\r\n	<span style="font-size: 16px;"><strong>&nbsp;</strong></span><u><strong>Prizes worth INR 30,000 to be won</strong></u></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;">\r\n	<span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><span style="font-family: trebuchet ms,helvetica,sans-serif;"><span style="font-size: 16px;"><strong>IGNITE YOUR PASSION<br />\r\n	</strong></span></span></span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;">\r\n	When fuel guzzling speed demons hit the track here at Quark 2011, maneuvering their way through dirt,rock and more,via whacky turns and tempting straights, through obstacles mean and along a tricky track,the game just raised its level&hellip;<br />\r\n	So get your cars to the line, Fireup your engines,hit the gas and nail those drifts square into tantalizing bends,conquer obstacles on your way to becoming India&rsquo;s top model ic car driver&hellip;.In the wild show out there,the fastest rider wins!..At this edition of Burnout,its all about precise control of machine and maniac..<br />\r\n	&nbsp;<span style="font-family: trebuchet ms,helvetica,sans-serif;"> <span style="font-size: 14px;"><strong>DO YOU DARE?</strong></span></span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;">\r\n	<span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;"><br />\r\n	</span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;">\r\n	<span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><span style="font-family: georgia,serif;"><u><strong>REGISTRATION FOR THE EVENT HAS ENDED </strong></u></span><u><strong><br />\r\n	</strong></u></span></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<span style="font-size: 12px;"><strong><br />\r\n	</strong></span></p>\r\n<table border="4" cellpadding="1" cellspacing="1" style="height: 143px; width: 423px;">\r\n	<thead>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<th scope="col">\r\n				<u><span style="font-family: georgia,serif;"><span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 205);">LATEST UPDATES</span><br />\r\n				</span></u></th>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</thead>\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style="text-align: center;">\r\n				<p>\r\n					<strong>Point system for round 3 updated. Check - Judging criteria<br />\r\n					</strong></p>\r\n				<p>\r\n					<a href="http://www.bits-quark.org/portal//img/uploads/quarkschedulerevised.jpg"><strong><u>Click here for Quark 2011 schedule<br />\r\n					</u></strong></a></p>\r\n				<p>\r\n					<a href="http://www.bits-quark.org/portal//img/uploads/Optimized-burnout.jpg"><u><strong>Click here for event poster</strong><br />\r\n					</u></a></p>\r\n				<p>\r\n					<u><span style="background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);"><span><strong>The list of RC car dealers from all over India has been added. Check&nbsp; - RESOURCES</strong></span></span></u></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>', '<p>\r\n	<span style="font-size: 12px;">&nbsp; </span></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<span style="font-family: georgia,serif;"><span style="font-size: 12px;"><span style="color: rgb(139, 69, 19);"><strong><span style="font-size: 14px;">Problem Statement</span></strong></span></span><br />\r\n	</span><br />\r\n	<strong>BURNOUT</strong> is an RC car event which will be held in<strong> 3 rounds</strong> with each team participating in all the 3 rounds.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<span style="font-size: 12px;">These rounds will judge the RC car in 4 different aspects :<br />\r\n	<br />\r\n	<strong><span style="font-size: 14px;"><span style="font-family: georgia,serif;">1</span></span>.</strong> Suspension System<br />\r\n	<br />\r\n	<strong><span style="font-family: georgia,serif;"><span style="font-size: 14px;">2</span></span>.</strong> Driving Skills</span></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<span style="font-size: 12px;"><strong><span style="font-size: 14px;"><span style="font-family: georgia,serif;">3</span></span>.</strong> Power</span></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<span style="font-size: 12px;"><strong><span style="font-family: georgia,serif;"><span style="font-size: 14px;">4</span></span>.</strong> Speed<br />\r\n	<br />\r\n	The points after each round will be calculated and summed up to a total out of <strong>200 points</strong>. At the end the winner will be decided according to the points obtained.<br />\r\n	<br />\r\n	</span><span style="font-family: georgia,serif;"><span style="font-size: 14px;"><span style="color: rgb(139, 69, 19);"><strong>Event Description</strong></span></span></span></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<span style="font-family: georgia,serif;"><span style="font-size: 14px;"><span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 255);"><strong>Round 1</strong></span></span></span></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<span style="font-family: georgia,serif;"><span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><strong>Drag race<br />\r\n	</strong></span></span></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	This round will take place on a straight track which will not contain any obstacle.Participants just need to make the car run as fast as possible.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<span style="font-size: 14px;"><span style="font-family: georgia,serif;"><span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 255);"><strong>Round 2</strong></span></span></span></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<span style="font-family: georgia,serif;"><span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><strong>Trailer Pulling </strong></span></span></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	In this round there will be a pulley system with a suitable weight at one end and the other end will be hooked to RC car. The RC car must pull the weight and reach the finish line.Teams reaching the finish line with minimum time will be awarded maximum points.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<span style="font-family: georgia,serif;"><span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 255);"><strong><span style="font-size: 14px;">Round</span> <span style="font-size: 14px;">3</span></strong></span></span></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<span style="font-family: georgia,serif;"><span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><strong>Track Race</strong></span></span></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	In this round RC cars of the participants will be made to race on a random shaped track.The track will also contain obstacles such as bumpers and pits.This track will test the suspension of the RC car.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<span style="font-size: 12px;"><span style="font-family: georgia,serif;"><span style="color: rgb(139, 69, 19);"><span style="font-size: 14px;"><b>Machine specifications<br />\r\n	</b></span></span></span><br />\r\n	<strong><span style="font-family: georgia,serif;"><span style="font-size: 14px;">1</span></span></strong>. The machine should fit in a box of dimensions 800 mm x 600 mm x 600 mm (l x b x h) at any moment of time during the race. The radio controller which is used to control the machine is not included in the size constraint.<br />\r\n	<br />\r\n	<strong><span style="font-family: georgia,serif;"><span style="font-size: 14px;">2</span></span></strong>. The machine should be controlled by a wireless remote control mechanism throughout the race.<br />\r\n	<br />\r\n	<strong><span style="font-family: georgia,serif;"><span style="font-size: 14px;">3</span></span></strong>. The machine must not be made from Lego parts, or any ready-made assembly kits other than the parts mentioned below. Readily available chassis layouts are not allowed. Any machine found having a ready-made chassis will be disqualified.<br />\r\n	<br />\r\n	<strong><span style="font-family: georgia,serif;"><span style="font-size: 14px;">4</span></span></strong>. The machine may be roughly classified into structural and functional parts:<br />\r\n	<br />\r\n	Functional parts - Gears, differential gear, engine, springs, shock absorbers, servo motors (non-propulsion purposes only), batteries, wheels and wheel hubs are allowed to be used as available in the market.<br />\r\n	<br />\r\n	Structural parts - Chassis, steering mechanism, shock towers and suspension (excluding upper suspension arm, suspension spring and shock absorbers) have to be built by the participants themselves.<br />\r\n	<br />\r\n	Judging for the same will be strict and the participant will be immediately disqualified if any of the above structural components are found to be ready-made.<br />\r\n	<br />\r\n	<strong><span style="font-family: georgia,serif;"><span style="font-size: 14px;">5</span></span></strong>. The tires used must have a minimum diameter of 2.5 inches. You are advised to use tyres of good width for better performance on dirt tracks.<br />\r\n	<br />\r\n	<strong><span style="font-family: georgia,serif;"><span style="font-size: 14px;">6</span></span></strong>. Wheel Hub: Any part rigidly attached to the wheel hub will be considered as a part of it and hence can be ready-made.<br />\r\n	<br />\r\n	<strong><span style="font-family: georgia,serif;"><span style="font-size: 14px;">7</span></span></strong>. If there are parts used in the concerned joint which are neither rigidly connected with the suspension, the steering system or the hub, ready-made parts from the market may be used.<br />\r\n	<br />\r\n	</span></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<span style="font-size: 12px;"><span style="font-family: georgia,serif;"><span style="color: rgb(139, 69, 19);"><span style="font-size: 14px;"><strong>Propulsion and steering</strong></span></span><br />\r\n	</span><br />\r\n	<span style="font-family: georgia,serif;"><span style="font-size: 14px;"><strong>1.</strong></span></span> The machine must use only mechanical power generated by an internal combustion (IC) engine for propulsion. Only one IC engine should be used in the machine. Use of any other sources such as chemicals, compressed gas, rockets etc. is not allowed.<br />\r\n	<br />\r\n	<span style="font-family: georgia,serif;"><strong><span style="font-size: 14px;">2.</span></strong></span> Any machine which uses DC Motors for propulsion will be disqualified. However DC motors and servos can be used for steering mechanisms or any other control mechanisms apart from propulsion.<br />\r\n	<br />\r\n	<span style="font-family: georgia,serif;"><strong><span style="font-size: 14px;">3.</span></strong></span> The machine must have an on-board power supply to run any mechanism requiring electric power.<br />\r\n	<br />\r\n	<strong><span style="font-family: georgia,serif;"><span style="font-size: 14px;">4.</span></span></strong> The maximum allowed capacity of IC engine to be used is 4.6 cc (i.e. Participants can also use 2.5 cc, 3 cc, 3.5 cc or any other IC engine lower in capacity).<br />\r\n	<br />\r\n	<strong><span style="font-family: georgia,serif;"><span style="font-size: 14px;">5.</span></span></strong> The electric voltage anywhere in the machine should not exceed 12V at any point of time.<br />\r\n	<br />\r\n	<strong><span style="font-family: georgia,serif;"><span style="font-size: 14px;">6</span></span></strong>. There shall be a countdown preceding the start of the race. No participant is allowed to touch the machine during the countdown period.<br />\r\n	<br />\r\n	<span style="font-family: georgia,serif;"><span style="font-size: 14px;"><strong>7</strong>.</span></span> Providing a clutch mechanism between the engine and the wheel would prove useful, as it would prevent the engine from dying out at any stage of the race.<br />\r\n	<br />\r\n	<span style="font-size: 14px;"><span style="font-family: georgia,serif;"><strong>8.</strong></span></span> Participants are advised to use a proper cooling mechanism to prevent overheating of the engine.<br />\r\n	<br />\r\n	<strong><span style="font-family: georgia,serif;"><span style="font-size: 14px;">9.</span></span></strong> Participants can use sway bars for better control and stability.<br />\r\n	<br />\r\n	<strong><span style="font-family: georgia,serif;"><span style="font-size: 14px;">10.</span></span></strong> The participants are advised to use proper air filters as dirt might cause serious problems to the engine.<br />\r\n	<br />\r\n	<strong><span style="font-family: georgia,serif;"><span style="font-size: 14px;">11.</span></span></strong> Readymade wheels are allowed.<br />\r\n	<br />\r\n	<strong><span style="font-family: georgia,serif;"><span style="font-size: 14px;">12.</span></span></strong> The machine will be inspected and if found to be dangerous, the team will be disqualified. This decision rests solely with the judges and the organizers.<br />\r\n	<br />\r\n	</span><span style="font-size: 12px;"><a href="http://www.bits-quark.org/portal//img/uploads/event_round2.jpg"><b><br />\r\n	</b></a></span></p>\r\n', 'burnout', '4af9dd07-f94c-42fb-ad6d-1064bb1aea99', '<p>\r\n	<span style="font-family: georgia,serif;"><span style="color: rgb(139, 69, 19);"><span style="font-size: 14px;"><strong>Game rules</strong><br />\r\n	</span></span></span><br />\r\n	<strong><span style="font-family: georgia,serif;"><span style="font-size: 14px;">1.</span></span></strong> Each team will have to take part in all 3 rounds. There will be no qualification round.<br />\r\n	<br />\r\n	<strong><span style="font-family: georgia,serif;"><span style="font-size: 14px;">2.</span></span></strong> In any round&nbsp; if the machine goes out of the arena at any instance, a penalty of 5 points will be imposed on that team and&nbsp; the timer(wherever applicable) shall continue running.<br />\r\n	<br />\r\n	<span style="font-family: georgia,serif;"><strong>3.</strong></span> The machines are not allowed to leave any loose parts or any other part in the track or in the arena. Any machine disintegrating during either of the rounds will be disqualified.<br />\r\n	<br />\r\n	<span style="font-family: georgia,serif;"><span style="color: rgb(139, 69, 19);"><span style="font-size: 14px;"><strong>General &nbsp;Rules</strong></span></span><br />\r\n	</span><br />\r\n	<strong><span style="font-family: georgia,serif;"><span style="font-size: 14px;">1.</span></span></strong> Any team that is not ready at the specified time shall be disqualified automatically.<br />\r\n	<br />\r\n	<strong><span style="font-family: georgia,serif;"><span style="font-size: 14px;">2.</span></span></strong> The teams must adhere to the spirit of healthy competition. Judges reserve the right to disqualify any team indulged in misbehaviour.<br />\r\n	<br />\r\n	<strong><span style="font-family: georgia,serif;"><span style="font-size: 14px;">3.</span></span></strong> Judges decision shall be final and binding on all.<br />\r\n	<br />\r\n	<strong><span style="font-family: georgia,serif;"><span style="font-size: 14px;">4.</span></span></strong> The organizers reserves the right to change any or all of the above rules as they deem fit. Change in rules if any will be highlighted in the website and will be notified to the registered participants.</p>\r\n', '<p>\r\n	<span style="font-size: 12px;"><br />\r\n	<br />\r\n	Each team will take part in all the <strong>3 rounds</strong> and points of each round will be calculated and summed up to a total out of <strong>200</strong>.<br />\r\n	<br />\r\n	<span style="font-size: 14px;"><span style="font-family: georgia,serif;"><span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 255);"><strong>Round 1</strong></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<span style="font-family: georgia,serif;"><span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><span style="font-size: 12px;"><strong>Drag race</strong></span></span></span></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<span style="font-size: 12px;">This round will be of<strong> 50 points</strong>.</span></li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<span style="font-size: 12px;">Two teams will be on the track at a time.</span></li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<span style="font-size: 12px;">The timings for all the teams will be noted and the points will be awarded accordingly.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>\r\n	<span style="font-size: 12px;"><br />\r\n	The standings of each team and their points will be tabulated as follows :-</span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;">\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<table border="4" cellpadding="1" cellspacing="1" style="height: 229px; width: 344px;">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style="text-align: center;">\r\n				<span style="color: rgb(139, 69, 19);"><span style="font-size: 14px;"><span style="font-family: georgia,serif;"><strong>Standings</strong></span></span></span></td>\r\n			<td style="text-align: center;">\r\n				<span style="color: rgb(139, 69, 19);"><span style="font-size: 14px;"><span style="font-family: georgia,serif;"><strong>Points<br />\r\n				</strong></span></span></span></td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style="text-align: center;">\r\n				<span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><strong><span style="font-size: 14px;"><span style="font-family: georgia,serif;">1</span></span></strong></span></td>\r\n			<td style="text-align: center;">\r\n				<span style="font-size: 14px;"><span style="font-family: georgia,serif;"><span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><strong>50</strong></span></span></span></td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style="text-align: center;">\r\n				<span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><strong><span style="font-size: 14px;"><span style="font-family: georgia,serif;">2</span></span></strong></span></td>\r\n			<td style="text-align: center;">\r\n				<span style="font-size: 14px;"><span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><strong>40</strong></span></span></td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style="text-align: center;">\r\n				<span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><strong><span style="font-family: georgia,serif;"><span style="font-size: 14px;">3</span></span></strong></span></td>\r\n			<td style="text-align: center;">\r\n				<span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><strong><span style="font-family: georgia,serif;"><span style="font-size: 14px;">30</span></span></strong></span></td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style="text-align: center;">\r\n				<span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><strong><span style="font-family: georgia,serif;"><span style="font-size: 14px;">4</span></span></strong></span></td>\r\n			<td style="text-align: center;">\r\n				<span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><strong><span style="font-family: georgia,serif;"><span style="font-size: 14px;">25</span></span></strong></span></td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style="text-align: center;">\r\n				<span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><strong><span style="font-family: georgia,serif;"><span style="font-size: 14px;">5</span></span></strong></span></td>\r\n			<td style="text-align: center;">\r\n				<span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><strong><span style="font-family: georgia,serif;"><span style="font-size: 14px;">20</span></span></strong></span></td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style="text-align: center;">\r\n				<span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><strong><span style="font-family: georgia,serif;"><span style="font-size: 14px;">6</span></span></strong></span></td>\r\n			<td style="text-align: center;">\r\n				<span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><strong><span style="font-family: georgia,serif;"><span style="font-size: 14px;">18</span></span></strong></span></td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style="text-align: center;">\r\n				<span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><strong><span style="font-family: georgia,serif;"><span style="font-size: 14px;">7</span></span></strong></span></td>\r\n			<td style="text-align: center;">\r\n				<span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><strong><span style="font-family: georgia,serif;"><span style="font-size: 14px;">14</span></span></strong></span></td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style="text-align: center;">\r\n				<span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><strong><span style="font-family: georgia,serif;"><span style="font-size: 14px;">8</span></span></strong></span></td>\r\n			<td style="text-align: center;">\r\n				<span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><strong><span style="font-family: georgia,serif;"><span style="font-size: 14px;">10</span></span></strong></span></td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style="text-align: center;">\r\n				<span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><strong><span style="font-family: georgia,serif;"><span style="font-size: 14px;">9</span></span></strong></span></td>\r\n			<td style="text-align: center;">\r\n				<span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><strong><span style="font-family: georgia,serif;"><span style="font-size: 14px;">6</span></span></strong></span></td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style="text-align: center;">\r\n				<span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><strong><span style="font-family: georgia,serif;"><span style="font-size: 14px;">10</span></span></strong></span></td>\r\n			<td style="text-align: center;">\r\n				<span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><strong><span style="font-family: georgia,serif;"><span style="font-size: 14px;">1</span></span></strong></span></td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p>\r\n	<span style="font-size: 14px;"><span style="font-family: georgia,serif;"><span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 255);"><strong><br />\r\n	<br />\r\n	Round 2</strong></span></span></span></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<span style="font-family: georgia,serif;"><span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><strong><span style="font-size: 12px;">Trailer Pulling</span></strong></span></span></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<span style="font-size: 12px;">This round will be of <strong>50 points</strong>.</span></li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<span style="font-size: 12px;">Each car will have to pull a suitable weight and reach the finish line.</span></li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<span style="font-size: 12px;">The car reaching the finish line in minimum time will be given maximum point.</span></li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<span style="font-size: 12px;">The point system will be same as Round 1(as shown above).</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>\r\n	<span style="font-family: georgia,serif;"><span style="font-size: 14px;"><span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 255);"><strong>Round 3 </strong><br />\r\n	</span></span></span></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<span style="font-family: georgia,serif;"><span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><span style="font-size: 12px;"><strong>Track race </strong></span></span></span></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n		This round will be of <strong>100 points.</strong></li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		The teams will be divided into and will be made to race. Each team will race with other participants from the same group.&nbsp; The bottom 2 teams from each group will be eliminated and the remaining teams will qualify for the next stage of this round. ( Each group will have a minimum of 4 teams )</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		The teams qualified for the next stage will be again divided into groups and the same procedure will be followed until we get top 4 teams.</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		The top 4 teams will be made to race again and points will be given according to their position. ( Top 4 teams will get the maximum points for this round )</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Points will also be rewarded to teams getting eliminated. The number of points will depend on the stage of the round in which they get eliminated ( points for elimination in second stage &gt; points for elimination in first stage. )</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		For example 25 teams are participating in last round , then the teams will be divided into groups of 5. Therefore the&nbsp; points system will be as follows :</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<table border="5" cellpadding="1" cellspacing="1" style="height: 557px; width: 369px;">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style="text-align: center;">\r\n				<span style="color: rgb(139, 69, 19);"><span style="font-family: georgia,serif;"><strong>Eliminated in stage</strong></span></span></td>\r\n			<td style="text-align: center;">\r\n				<span style="color: rgb(139, 69, 19);"><span style="font-family: georgia,serif;"><strong>Points <br />\r\n				</strong></span></span></td>\r\n			<td style="text-align: center;">\r\n				<span style="color: rgb(139, 69, 19);"><span style="font-family: georgia,serif;"><strong>Description<br />\r\n				</strong></span></span></td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style="text-align: center;">\r\n				<span style="font-family: georgia,serif;"><strong>1</strong></span></td>\r\n			<td style="text-align: center;">\r\n				<span style="font-family: georgia,serif;"><strong>0<br />\r\n				</strong></span></td>\r\n			<td>\r\n				In&nbsp; stage 1, out of <strong>25</strong> teams <strong>15</strong> will qualify for next stage and <strong>10</strong> teams will be eliminated.The <strong>10 </strong>teams which will be eliminated will be awarded no points.</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style="text-align: center;">\r\n				<span style="font-family: georgia,serif;"><strong>2</strong></span></td>\r\n			<td style="text-align: center;">\r\n				<span style="font-family: georgia,serif;"><strong>30<br />\r\n				</strong></span></td>\r\n			<td>\r\n				In&nbsp; stage 2, teams will again be divided into groups of <strong>5</strong>.Out of <strong>15</strong> teams<strong> 9</strong> teams will qualify for next stage and the other <strong>6 </strong>teams will be eliminated.The eliminated teams will be awarded with <strong>30</strong> points.</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style="text-align: center;">\r\n				<span style="font-family: georgia,serif;"><strong>3</strong></span></td>\r\n			<td style="text-align: center;">\r\n				<span style="font-family: georgia,serif;"><strong>50<br />\r\n				</strong></span></td>\r\n			<td>\r\n				In stage 3, teams will be divided into<strong> 2</strong> groups of <strong>4 </strong>and<strong> 5 </strong>teams respectively .Out of <strong>9</strong> teams<strong> 5</strong> will qualify for next stage and the other<strong> 4</strong> teams will be eliminated.The eliminated teams will be awarded <strong>50</strong> points.</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style="text-align: center;">\r\n				<span style="font-family: georgia,serif;"><strong>4</strong></span></td>\r\n			<td style="text-align: center;">\r\n				<span style="font-family: georgia,serif;"><strong>70<br />\r\n				</strong></span></td>\r\n			<td>\r\n				In&nbsp; final stage 4, there will be only one group and the teams except the top <strong>3</strong> teams will be awarded<strong> 70</strong> points. The other <strong>3</strong> teams will be awarded <strong>100</strong>,<strong>90</strong> and <strong>80</strong> points according to their standings in this round.</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p>\r\n	<span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 128);"><strong><span style="font-size: 16px;">Note : </span></strong></span><span style="font-size: 14px;"><span style="font-family: georgia,serif;">The number of stages in this round will depend on the number of teams participating in the event. Hence the point system will also change with number of participating teams.</span></span></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<span style="color: rgb(139, 69, 19);"><u><br />\r\n	</u></span></p>\r\n', '<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Here are some resources given for your help .</p>\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<a href="http://www.bits-quark.org/portal//files/INTRODUCTION_TO_ICENGINE.pdf ">IC Engine<br />\r\n		</a></li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<a href="http://www.bits-quark.org/portal//files/SUSPENSION..pdf ">Suspension <br />\r\n		</a></li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<a href="http://www.bits-quark.org/portal//files/CHASSIS_FABRICATION_AND_STEERING_MECHANISM.pdf ">Chassis building and steering mechanism<br />\r\n		</a></li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<a href="http://www.bits-quark.org/portal//files/RCDEALERS.pdf">List of RC car dealers</a></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n', '<p>\r\n	If you have any query, please send an e-mail to <strong>burnout@bits-quark.org</strong> or get in touch with any one of us:</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<span style="font-size: 14px;"><span style="font-family: times new roman,times,serif;"><strong>Saikat Mitra<br />\r\n	+91 9561649486<br />\r\n	<br />\r\n	Shaurya Sachdev<br />\r\n	+91 9637423516&nbsp;<br />\r\n	<br />\r\n	</strong></span></span></p>\r\n', 1, 5);
INSERT INTO `events` (`id`, `name`, `intro`, `details`, `route`, `category_id`, `rules`, `judging_criteria`, `additional_info`, `contact`, `min_participants`, `max_participants`) VALUES
('4cbc7331-fc40-4f41-8dce-05d80a030849', 'TACK IT 2.0', '<p>\r\n	When engineers communicate, it is not the words that flow. Without technical drawings and models, ideas would not have come off the paper to be later transformed into marvels. Even the best design idea is worthless if the designer cannot convey it to the production personnel. In times like these, it becomes even more critical to provide engineers with collaborative tools that will help rethink today&#39;s landscape and tighten community around a common goal. Pro-E fits this bill perfectly.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Pro-Engineer is the core mechanical software which is used by many manufacturers in designing and manufacturing. Due to its very user-friendly interface and accuracy, companies use pro-engineer to create complete 3D models of their products. Additionally, due to bidirectional associative property, users are able to make changes in their design at any time and automatically update the assembly.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Pro-Engineer supports users to create virtual mechanisms that answer general questions in product-design. The modelling and analytical capabilities of Pro-Engineer will help to answer common questions of designers&rsquo; minds accurately and realistically, as long as the motion model is properly defined. Pro- engineer will also help you to search for better alternatives. So,</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Get ready, empower your teams and have a larger number of ideas coming to life.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Entirely convey your design intent all the way through from initial ideation to engineering, manufacturing and design.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<u><strong>Prizes worth INR 10,000 to be won.</strong></u></p>\r\n', '<p>\r\n	<link href="file:///C:%5CUsers%5Cpranay%5CAppData%5CLocal%5CTemp%5COICE_9EC230FD-0703-463E-B2FA-2815A5C7CE76.0%5Cmsohtmlclip1%5C01%5Cclip_filelist.xml" rel="File-List" /><!--[if gte mso 9]><xml>\r\n <o:OfficeDocumentSettings>\r\n  <o:RelyOnVML/>\r\n  <o:AllowPNG/>\r\n </o:OfficeDocumentSett