al">\r\n	<span style="font-size: 14px"><span style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif"><span style="line-height: 115%"><strong>Event Format</strong></span></span></span>:<span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span><o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal">\r\n	The event consists of 2 rounds. Both the rounds are on-campus. 1<sup>st</sup> round is a basic round which will test the basic skills of participants in Pro-Engineer which will be of around one or one and half hours. They will be given some assembly which they are supposed to complete within stipulated time. <span>&nbsp;</span>The problem statement for 2<sup>nd </sup>round is as follows:<span style="line-height: 115%; font-size: 14pt"><o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal">\r\n	<span style="font-size: 14px"><strong><span style="line-height: 115%">Problem Statement</span></strong>:</span> To design, assemble, and run a mechanism which has some flaws in it. Identify those faults and modify them so that mechanism runs successfully.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal">\r\n	<font class="Apple-style-span" size="6"><span class="Apple-style-span" style="line-height: 21px; font-size: 19px"><br />\r\n	</span></font></p>\r\n', 'ingeniur', '4af9dd07-f94c-42fb-ad6d-1064bb1aea99', '<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="text-indent: -18pt; margin-left: 20.25pt">\r\n	<span style="line-height: 18px; font-size: 12pt"><span style="font-size: 12px">A</span></span><span style="font-size: 12px">)</span>&nbsp;<strong><span style="font-size: 12px">General</span></strong><strong>:</strong><span style="line-height: 21px; font-size: 14pt"><o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<span style="color: black">A student can represent only one team and cannot be a part of more than one team</span></li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<span class="Apple-style-span" style="color: rgb(0,0,0)">Any number of teams can participate from the same college</span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-left: 2.25pt">\r\n	<span style="font-family: arial, sans-serif; color: black"><span style="font-size: 12px">B)</span><span style="font-size: 16px"> <strong><span style="font-size: 12px">Event Rules</span></strong></span><strong>:</strong></span></p>\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<span class="Apple-style-span" style="color: rgb(0,0,0)">Rules for both the on campus rounds will be given on the spot.</span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n', '<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Each complete figure will be assigned with points which are specified in the problem statement.</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Number of steps and the commands used will be taken into consideration.</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Identification of fault and its modification will carry specific marks.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n', '<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal">\r\n	<span class="Apple-style-span" style="line-height: 19px"><b><br />\r\n	</b></span></p>\r\n', '<p class="MsoNormal">\r\n	<span class="Apple-style-span" style="line-height: 18px; font-family: arial; color: rgb(0,0,0)">If you have any query, please send an e-mail to&nbsp;<br />\r\n	<strong>tackit@bits-quark.org</strong>, or get in touch with any one of us:</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal">\r\n	<strong><span style="font-size: 12px"><span style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif"><span style="line-height: 18px">Paresh Prabhudesai</span></span></span></strong></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal">\r\n	<strong><span style="font-size: 12px"><span style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif"><span style="line-height: 18px"><span class="Apple-style-span" style="font-weight: normal">+91-9420750248</span></span></span></span></strong></p>\r\n', 1, 3);
