the run) + (Time penalty for skipping the bridge = 10 seconds) +(Penalty for not stopping at penalty point=15 seconds)</span></span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal">\r\n	<span style="font-size: 12px;"><span style="line-height: 115%;">The qualifiers are decided in the increasing order of total score (team with minimum score wins)</span></span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal">\r\n	<span style="font-size: 12px;"><b style=""><span style="line-height: 115%;">&nbsp;</span></b></span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal">\r\n	<span style="font-size: 12px;"><b style=""><span style="line-height: 115%;">Round 2:</span></b></span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal">\r\n	<span style="font-size: 12px;"><span style="line-height: 115%;">Final Score S<b style=""> </b>= (Total time taken for completion of the run) + (Time penalty for passing a penalty = 15 seconds)+</span></span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal">\r\n	<span style="font-size: 14pt; line-height: 115%;"><span style="font-size: 12px;">The team with the minimum score wins</span>.</span></p>\r\n', '<p>\r\n	<strong>Certification Policy:<br />\r\n	Certificate of Excellence</strong>: Awarded to the top 3 teams of the final round.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<strong>Certificate of Merit:</strong> Awarded to teams who complete round 2</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<strong>Certificate of Participation</strong>: Awarded to &nbsp;teams who complete round1.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<strong>Resources:</strong></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dijkstra''s_algorithm">http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dijkstra&#39;s_algorithm</a></p>\r\n', '<p>\r\n	If you have any query, please send an e-mail to <strong>citymaps@bits-quark.org</strong>, or get in touch with any one of us:</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<strong>Aditya M. Dixit</strong><br />\r\n	+919833051669</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<strong>Shubhankar Mitra</strong><br />\r\n	+919545584951</p>\r\n', 0, 4),
('4cbc76f7-4764-442d-b527-05d80a030849', 'RoboKombat', '<p style="text-align: right;">\r\n	<u><strong>Prizes worth INR 25,000 to be won.</strong></u></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;">\r\n	<strong>Destroy | Survive | Win<br />\r\n	</strong></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;">\r\n	&hellip;&rdquo;<span style="font-size: 14px;"><em>When India&rsquo;s deadliest battle bots take to one another with all they have,<br />\r\n	Flame,Flipper,Saw and Ax,<br />\r\n	carnage and annihilation are at their MAX!</em></span>&rdquo;&hellip;<br />\r\n	<br />\r\n	Come this Quark, RoboKombat is bigger, better and many times more destructive&hellip;expect nothing less than the ultimate in robot wars, as elite teams from all over the nation go head to head with the lethal combo of engineering and pure destructive intent put to an explosive mix. Featuring a new format from <em>King Of The Ring</em> at Quark &#39;10, more than just sparks will fly on this arena&hellip; No Mercy...Just one survivor....</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;">\r\n	Be a part of this full on fight to the death! <a href="http://www.bits-quark.org/portal/users/participate/4cbc76f7-4764-442d-b527-05d80a030849">Register now!</a></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;">\r\n	<a href="http://www.bits-quark.org/portal/img/uploads/RoboKombat_PosterV2.png" onclick="window.open(this.href, ''RoboKombat @ Quark 2011'', ''resizable=yes,status=no,location=no,toolbar=no,menubar=no,fullscreen=yes,scrollbars=yes,dependent=no''); return false;">Check Out the Event Poster </a></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;">\r\n	<img alt="&lt;New!&gt;" height="42" src="http://img10.imageshack.us/img10/6708/badgeneworange.gif" width="42" /><strong>Rules</strong> &amp; <strong>Resources</strong> have been updated</p>\r\n', '<p>\r\n	The challenge is to build a wireless or manually controlled wired bot which can drive out the opponent&rsquo;s bot out of the ring .The bot can drag, push or throw the opponent&rsquo;s bot out of the ring.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	The arena pics are given here as under:</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<strong>Round-1:</strong></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<img alt="" fix="fixed" height="229" src="http://www.bits-quark.org/portal/img/uploads/ArenaR1-2.png " style="width: 321px; height: 181px;" width="480" /></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	To get a clearer idea of the 1st Round, see this <a href="http://picasaweb.google.com/kmmankad/Round1Description#slideshow/5555161081048861266">slideshow</a>.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<strong>Round 2</strong></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<img alt="" fix="fixed" height="421" src="http://www.bits-quark.org/portal/img/uploads/robokombat2.png" style="width: 381px; height: 421px;" width="381" /></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Download the <a href="http://www.bits-quark.org/portal/img/uploads/ArenaPics.zip ">Full Size Arena Pics</a></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<strong>Event Format:<br />\r\n	Round 1 &ndash; &ldquo;Show your Might</strong>&rdquo;<br />\r\n	1.&nbsp;The arena for the 1st round will be a simple hexagon of 2 m diagonal.<br />\r\n	2.&nbsp;The bots will take part in a &ldquo;tug of war&rdquo; match, for which details of the exact arrangement can be viewed here.<br />\r\n	3. All the bots will be divided into pools and each bot will have a match with every other bot in that pool.<br />\r\n	4. Time limit for each match in this round will be 3 mins. Any match without a proper result within the time limit will be declared as a tie.<br />\r\n	5. Winning bot qualifies to the next round. <br />\r\n	6. The Time limit for the round shall be specified at the time of event.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <br />\r\n	7. At any level of the match, damaging the opponent&rsquo;s wires or the plywood arena will lead to immediate disqualification. In this round bots are not allowed to destroy the opponent.<br />\r\n	8. Any other discrepancies shall be resolved by the EMs on the spot.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<strong>Round 2 &ndash;&ldquo;Survival of the fittest&rdquo;</strong></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	1. The arena for the 2nd round will be a simple hexagon of 3m diagonal. The 2nd round will be a knock-out round.<br />\r\n	2. The bots qualified to this round will be put into different groups randomly.<br />\r\n	3. The points from round1 will carry over to the 2nd round.<br />\r\n	4. There will be a single match between all the members of the group .Bots in each group have to fight with all other bots simultaneously. The time limit for each fight in round 2 will be declared at the time of event.<br />\r\n	5. The winner of each group will proceed to the 3rd round.<br />\r\n	6. At any stage of the fight, damaging the opponent&rsquo;s wires or the plywood arena will lead to immediate disqualification. But any other type of destruction will be allowed.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<strong>Round 3-&ldquo;The Finale&rdquo;<br />\r\n	</strong>1. There will be a single match with all the finalists fighting together in an arena.Each bot has to push, drag or throw their opponent out of the ring. The arena dimensions will not be disclosed prior to the event. The arena will have its own surprises and weapons.<br />\r\n	2. There is no time limit for this round. The match will go on till only 1 bot is left in the arena.<br />\r\n	3. At any level of the fight, damaging the opponent&#39;s wires or the arena will lead to immediate disqualification. But destruction of any other kind is allowed.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<strong>BOT SPECIFICATION<br />\r\n	</strong>1. The bot can be wired or wireless. Wireless bots should have at least two modes of frequency to avoid frequency interference.<br />\r\n	2. The controlling wires should be bound into a single strip and long enough, it should not entangle with the opponent&#39;s wires. The length of the wire from the bot to the controlling unit (switch board) should be more than 4m.The wire should always remain slack throughout the competition.<br />\r\n	3. <strong>Maximum size of the robot should be 40 cm x 40 cm x 40cm.(The bot will be checked for its specifications before it enters into the tournament and any failure to comply with event rules(specifically weight and dimension of the bot) will lead to disqualification. The bot can have expanding arms,but at NO point during the match,should the dimensions exceed said limits of size.)</strong><br />\r\n	4. The participating teams are allowed to use any sort of weapons. The teams should ensure that the weapons are <em>safe for the spectators and the arena</em>.[Weapons involving fire or a liquid/gel of any kind that may damage the arena are NOT allowed]. The organizers have the right to disqualify the team with unsafe weapons.<br />\r\n	5. The potential difference between any two points should not exceed 24V.<br />\r\n	6. <strong>The total weight of bot should not exceed 7 kg on the arena.</strong></p>\r\n', 'robokombat', '4af9dd54-68fc-4cdf-b8da-1064bb1aea99', '<p>\r\n	<strong>GENERAL RULES:<br />\r\n	</strong>1. The maximum number of members allowed per team is 4 (four) and minimum is 1 (one).<br />\r\n	2. Participants are allowed to use any sort of weapons in the bot. The participants should make sure that weapons used should be safe for the spectators and the arena. The organizers have the right to disqualify the team with unsafe weapons.<br />\r\n	3. 230V AC Power supply will be provided. The participating teams should bring adaptors/eliminators of the required voltage rating.<br />\r\n	<strong>4. An abstract, explaining the bot design should be mailed to the event managers <u>by 25th January 2011</u>. (mail-id as given under Contacts).The abstract must contain,</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<strong>A Sketch/Picture/Video of the Bot.<br />\r\n		</strong></li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<strong>Complete details of the dimensions of the Bot.<br />\r\n		</strong></li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<strong>A Brief explanation of the weapons system used.<br />\r\n		</strong></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>\r\n	5. All the participating teams are requested to be at the venue on time. Date and time will be put up on the site.<br />\r\n	6. The organizers have the right to change the rules as and when required.Change in rules, if any, will be highlighted on the website and notified to the registered participants.<br />\r\n	7. The event managers&rsquo; decision regarding scoring and judgment will be final.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<strong><br />\r\n	Competition Rules<br />\r\n	</strong>1. <u><strong>The bot will be checked for its specifications before it enters into the tournament and any failure to comply with event rules(specifically weight and dimension of the bot) will lead to disqualification. The bot can have expanding arms,but at NO point during the match,should the dimensions exceed said limits of 40cm x 40cm x 40cm.</strong></u></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	2.<u><strong>Participants are expected 2 keep the length of the wires from remote to bot atleast 3 meters</strong></u><br />\r\n	3. Teams using wireless control are advised to use at least two frequencies on their remote control to <em>avoid frequency jamming.</em><br />\r\n	4. No extra time will be provided to the team for repair of the bot once the competition starts. However, teams may repair their bots in between the rounds.<br />\r\n	5. The bot must be ready by the time the team is called for the event.<br />\r\n	6. The time limit for Round-1 will be 3 minutes.<br />\r\n	7. The time limit for Round-2 will be declared on the spot.<br />\r\n	8. There is no time limit for Round-3. The match will go on till, only 1 bot is left in the arena.<br />\r\n	9. Any kind of unfair play during the match will lead to immediate disqualification.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<br />\r\n	<strong>Certification Policy:</strong><br />\r\n	Participation certificate shall be awarded to all participants.<br />\r\n	Certificate of Excellence shall be awarded to the top 3 teams.<br />\r\n	<strong><br />\r\n	<br />\r\n	Eligibility:<br />\r\n	</strong>All students with a valid identity card of their respective educational institutes are eligible to participate in this event.<br />\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '', '<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<img alt="&lt;New!&gt;" height="42" src="http://img10.imageshack.us/img10/6708/badgeneworange.gif" width="42" />To get a clearer idea of the 1st Round, see <a href="http://picasaweb.google.com/kmmankad/Round1Description#slideshow/5555161081048861266">this </a><a href="http://picasaweb.google.com/kmmankad/Round1Description#slideshow/5555161081048861266" target="Round1">slideshow</a> (If you arent able to view the slideshow,you may <a href="http://www.bits-quark.org/portal/img/uploads/RoboKombat_Round_1.zip ">download it</a>).</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<img alt="&lt;New!&gt;" height="42" src="http://img10.imageshack.us/img10/6708/badgeneworange.gif" width="42" />Useful Tips &amp; Ideas <a href="http://www.bits-quark.org/portal/files/RoboKombat_TipsIdeas.pdf "><u><span style="text-decoration: underline;">- Download the pdf</span></u></a></li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Technical Guide to Building Fighting Robots&ndash;(<a href="http://robots.freehostia.com/">http://robots.freehostia.com/</a> )</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Download the <a href="http://www.bits-quark.org/portal/img/uploads/ArenaPics.zip ">Full Size Arena Pics</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>\r\n	A more technical site devoted to the contruction of combat robots. If you already know something about robotics or other R/C hobbies this will help you get a grip on fighting them.<br />\r\n	Lots more info and links here &ndash; <br />\r\n	<a href="http://robots.freehostia.com/Links/Links.html">http://robots.freehostia.com/Links/Links.html</a></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<img alt="&lt;New!&gt;" height="42" src="http://img10.imageshack.us/img10/6708/badgeneworange.gif" width="42" />A Lookback at last year&#39;s &#39;King Of the Ring&#39; :</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>\r\n	Day 1</p>\r\n<div style="width: 288px; font-family: arial,sans-serif; font-size: 13px;">\r\n	<div>\r\n		<embed flashvars="host=picasaweb.google.com&amp;hl=en_US&amp;feat=flashalbum&amp;RGB=0x000000&amp;feed=http%3A%2F%2Fpicasaweb.google.com%2Fdata%2Ffeed%2Fapi%2Fuser%2F113311583957866202295%2Falbumid%2F5554058410953852865%3Falt%3Drss%26kind%3Dphoto%26hl%3Den_US" height="192" pluginspage="http://www.macromedia.com/go/getflashplayer" src="http://picasaweb.google.com/s/c/bin/slideshow.swf" type="application/x-shockwave-flash" width="288"></embed></div>\r\n	<span style="float: left;"><a href="http://picasaweb.google.com/113311583957866202295/KingOfTheRingQuark2010DoPYDay1?feat=flashalbum" style="color: rgb(57, 100, 194);">View all</a></span>\r\n	<div style="text-align: right;">\r\n		&nbsp;</div>\r\n	<p>\r\n		Day 2</p>\r\n	<div style="width: 288px; font-family: arial,sans-serif; font-size: 13px;">\r\n		<div>\r\n			<embed flashvars="host=picasaweb.google.com&amp;hl=en_US&amp;feat=flashalbum&amp;RGB=0x000000&amp;feed=http%3A%2F%2Fpicasaweb.google.com%2Fdata%2Ffeed%2Fapi%2Fuser%2F113311583957866202295%2Falbumid%2F5554786799737839009%3Falt%3Drss%26kind%3Dphoto%26hl%3Den_US" height="192" pluginspage="http://www.macromedia.com/go/getflashplayer" src="http://picasaweb.google.com/s/c/bin/slideshow.swf" type="application/x-shockwave-flash" width="288"></embed></div>\r\n		<span style="float: left;"><a href="http://picasaweb.google.com/113311583957866202295/KingOfRingQuark2010DoPYDay2?feat=flashalbum" style="color: rgb(57, 100, 194);">View all</a></span>\r\n		<div style="text-align: right;">\r\n			&nbsp;</div>\r\n	</div>\r\n</div>\r\n', '<p>\r\n	For any queries/feedback or similar,&nbsp; send an e-mail to <strong><br />\r\n	robokombat@bits-quark.org</strong>, or get in touch with any one of us:</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<strong>Venkateswaran A</strong>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<strong> </strong><br />\r\n	+91 9049654259&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <br />\r\n	<strong><br />\r\n	Kartik Mankad</strong>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <br />\r\n	+91 9503817805&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<strong> </strong></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<strong>Juhi Khattar<br />\r\n	</strong>+91 9370879700<br />\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n', 1, 4),
('4cbc777b-de80-4ff1-b103-05d80a030849', 'The Amazing Race', '<p>\r\n	The biggest event in Quark is back, and this time with new challenges to tantalize your brain. With more than 400 participants in Quark &#39;10 and promises to get even bigger, it&#39;s bound to eke out every small component of your knowledge pool. So pit your skills against the very best and brace yourself for a breathtaking 3-day journey. The contestants will be tested in general knowledge, science, business,technology,&nbsp; and various other topics plus a really good&nbsp; eye for&nbsp; little things around you that most people won&#39;t look twice at.&nbsp; The fastest to crack the puzzle and find the treasures stands&nbsp; to win prizes worth thousands.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<span style="font-size:14px;"><br />\r\n	</span></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<span style="font-size:14px;"><u><strong>Prizes worth INR 10,000 to be won.</strong></u></span></p>\r\n', '<p>\r\n	<strong>Structure:</strong></p>\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n		The entire institute will be mapped into seven regions as shown in a given map. The seven regions represent seven levels that you have to attain to complete the race.</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Participants will be first provided with a puzzle question, usually a visual connect question, for which they are to give a &#39;Connect&#39; which is a single word or a sentence that links all the items in the puzzle shown to you. You can give the anwer immediately, or choose to answer later. You can also skip the question for a penalty.</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		On answering, you proceed to&nbsp; the treasure round.In the treasure&nbsp; round,&nbsp; you will be shown a picture of a specific item in the your assigned region of the&nbsp; campus. You are to search the region, find the item, and and return to us with proof of the finding(preferably a picture of you with the item or at the location)</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		If we find the proof to be valid, we will tally points to your team.</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		After the treasure round, you will have an option to attempt a bonus question, for extra score. If chosen, the question HAS to be answered correctly for points. Wrong answers, or lack of an answer will attract a penalty. Otherwise you proceed to the next level</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Each of the seven levels will have the same structure mentioned above.</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Exact&nbsp; details of the reward system, and more information will be provided when you register.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n', 'amazingrace', '4af9dd89-e1c0-48e3-9ab7-1064bb1aea99', '<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n		You are expected to register for the event on the Quark website. We will pull your details automatically. On-the-spot registrations are also allowed.</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Teams are expected to carry</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Teams can enter the game at any point of time. Since the daily prizes are not dependant on the cumulative score, teams are encouraged to participate even if they can&#39;t make it on the first day of Quark 2011.</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Each participating team will start with zero points and gather points as they crack questions and collect clues during the day</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		The points from each day will not carry forward to the next day, but will be used to determine the Overall Winner and runners-up</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		The top three teams will be given daily prizes at the end of each day.</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		In case of ties in scores , the time in which the teams finished&nbsp; will be used to break the ties.</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		We have designed the event such that each team gets different clues, routes, and puzzles. Even so, teams found guilty disfiguring clues, cheating, or helping other teams out, will be disqualified immediately.</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Teams are expected to be aware of the above rules, and those with&nbsp; any doubts or clarifications may freely&nbsp; contact the managers.</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		In the event of any dispute/confusion, the decision of the Event Managers will be FINAL</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n', '<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n		The top scoring&nbsp; three teams will be given daily prizes at the end of each day.</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		The points from each day will not carry forward to the next day, but will be used to determine the Overall Winners</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		The Overall Winners are the teams with maximum cumulative scores over the three days of the event</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		In case of ties in scores at any point , the time in which the teams finished&nbsp; will be used to break the ties.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n', '<p>\r\n	<strong><br />\r\n	Certification Policy:</strong></p>\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Each day&rsquo;s winners will be given Excellence Certificates.</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		The next two teams from each day will be give Merit Certificates.</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		The remaining 7 Runners Up will be given participation certificates.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n', '<div>\r\n	If you have any query, please send an e-mail to <strong>amazingrace@bits-quark.org</strong> or get in touch with any one of us:</div>\r\n<p>\r\n	<strong>Sunil Thomas</strong><br />\r\n	+91 9049268996</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<strong>Kasturi M Bhardwaj</strong><br />\r\n	+91 9049442480<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space: pre"> </span></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<strong><br />\r\n	</strong><span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space: pre"> </span></p>\r\n', 2, 4);
