('4cbc77b6-45f0-4a9f-a359-05d80a030849', 'M.A.D', '<h2>\r\n	(Marketing, Advertising and Design)</h2>\r\n<p>\r\n	Think, thinking out of the box in a given time constraint sounds easy? Test your mettle at M.A.D!<br />\r\n	The event will test your creativity, innovation, originality, marketing and promotional skills, along with your zest and technical skills for Photoshop and video making.&nbsp;There is NO prerequisite for participation in this event except for passion and familiarity with Adobe Photoshop.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<u><strong>ONLINE ROUND</strong></u>: <a href="http://www.bits-quark.org/portal/files/MAD_prob_statement.pdf" target="_blank">Click here</a> to download the problem statement.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<u><strong>Prizes worth INR 12,000 to be won.</strong></u></p>\r\n', '<div>\r\n	<span class="Apple-style-span" style="background-color: rgb(255,255,255)">M.A.D is an &nbsp;event that basically aims at testing the creative and technical skills of the &nbsp;participants . The participants will be asked to make a short video in the pre-Quark round, advertising a particular product (details will be announced soon). &nbsp;In the on campus round they will be asked to design a poster promoting a particular product given to them at that moment.</span></div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	The event comprises of two rounds as follows:</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	<strong><span class="Apple-style-span" style="background-color: rgb(255,255,255)">Round 1&nbsp;(The Pre -Quark Round):</span></strong></div>\r\n<div>\r\n	<p>\r\n		<span class="Apple-style-span" style="background-color: rgb(255,255,255)"><span class="Apple-style-span" style="background-color: rgb(255,255,255)">Make a short video advertising a particular product. This must be submitted by the participant when they come to campus. The details of the product will be provided some time before the first round begins (keep checking this space for details).</span></span></p>\r\n	<p>\r\n		<u><strong>ONLINE ROUND</strong></u>:&nbsp;<a href="http://www.bits-quark.org/portal/files/MAD_prob_statement.pdf" target="_blank">Click here</a>&nbsp;to download the problem statement.</p>\r\n	<p>\r\n		<span class="Apple-style-span" style="background-color: rgb(255,255,255)"><strong><span class="Apple-style-span" style="background-color: rgb(255,255,255)"><span class="Apple-style-span" style="background-color: rgb(255,255,255)">Round 2 (On Campus Round):<br />\r\n		</span></span></strong></span></p>\r\n	<p>\r\n		<span class="Apple-style-span" style="background-color: rgb(255,255,255)"><span class="Apple-style-span" style="background-color: rgb(255,255,255)"><span class="Apple-style-span" style="background-color: rgb(255,255,255)">The participants must design a poster advertising a specific product. The details of the product to be promoted will be given on the spot. The participants are free to use the internet for pictures or any other relevant content.</span></span></span></p>\r\n</div>\r\n', 'mad', '4af9dd89-e1c0-48e3-9ab7-1064bb1aea99', '<p>\r\n	<strong><span class="Apple-style-span" style="background-color: rgb(255,255,255)">Round 1&nbsp;(The Online&nbsp;<span class="Apple-style-span" style="font-weight: normal"><strong>Pre-Quark R<span class="Apple-style-span" style="font-weight: normal"><strong><span class="Apple-style-span" style="background-color: rgb(255,255,255)">ound):</span></strong></span></strong></span></span></strong></p>\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<span class="Apple-style-span" style="background-color: rgb(255,255,255)">The duration of the video should be less than 60 seconds.<br />\r\n		</span></li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<span class="Apple-style-span" style="background-color: rgb(255,255,255)">Any video editing software may be used.</span></li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<span class="Apple-style-span" style="background-color: rgb(255,255,255)">The video should be in .avi, .mpeg, .mpg , .mp4 formats only.<br />\r\n		</span></li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<span class="Apple-style-span" style="background-color: rgb(255,255,255)">The video will be judged on the creativity and execution, not the quality of the video.</span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p>\r\n	<strong><span class="Apple-style-span" style="background-color: rgb(255,255,255)"><span class="Apple-style-span" style="background-color: rgb(255,255,255)">Round 2 (<span class="Apple-style-span" style="font-weight: normal"><strong>On Campus Round)<span class="Apple-style-span" style="font-weight: normal"><strong><span class="Apple-style-span" style="background-color: rgb(255,255,255)"><span class="Apple-style-span" style="background-color: rgb(255,255,255)">:</span></span></strong></span></strong></span></span></span></strong></p>\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<span class="Apple-style-span" style="background-color: rgb(255,255,255)"><span class="Apple-style-span" style="background-color: rgb(255,255,255)">The software to be used is Adobe Photoshop CS4 or higher.</span></span></li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<span class="Apple-style-span" style="background-color: rgb(255,255,255)"><span class="Apple-style-span" style="background-color: rgb(255,255,255)">The poster size should be A3.</span></span></li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<span class="Apple-style-span" style="background-color: rgb(255,255,255)"><span class="Apple-style-span" style="background-color: rgb(255,255,255)">If you are using images as part of your poster, do not use them directly as they are.</span></span></li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<span class="Apple-style-span" style="background-color: rgb(255,255,255)"><span class="Apple-style-span" style="background-color: rgb(255,255,255)">Your PSD files will be checked for original work.</span></span></li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<span class="Apple-style-span" style="background-color: rgb(255,255,255)"><span class="Apple-style-span" style="background-color: rgb(255,255,255)">You are required to submit your PSD file.</span></span></li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<span class="Apple-style-span" style="background-color: rgb(255,255,255)"><span class="Apple-style-span" style="background-color: rgb(255,255,255)">Please ensure that you do not merge all your layers (flatten) of your PSD file.</span></span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n', '<p>\r\n	<span class="Apple-style-span" style="background-color: rgb(255,255,255)">In<strong> Round 1</strong>, the event is a test of the following:</span></p>\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<span class="Apple-style-span" style="background-color: rgb(255,255,255)">Video Editing Skills<br />\r\n		</span></li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<span class="Apple-style-span" style="background-color: rgb(255,255,255)">Market Analysis<br />\r\n		</span></li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<span class="Apple-style-span" style="background-color: rgb(255,255,255)">Analytical Skills<br />\r\n		</span></li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<span class="Apple-style-span" style="background-color: rgb(255,255,255)">Innovation &amp; Creativity</span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<span class="Apple-style-span" style="background-color: rgb(255,255,255)"><span class="Apple-style-span" style="background-color: rgb(255,255,255)">In <strong>Round 2</strong>, the event is a test of the following:</span></span></p>\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<span class="Apple-style-span" style="background-color: rgb(255,255,255)"><span class="Apple-style-span" style="background-color: rgb(255,255,255)">&nbsp;Photoshop Skills&nbsp;</span></span></li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<span class="Apple-style-span" style="background-color: rgb(255,255,255)"><span class="Apple-style-span" style="background-color: rgb(255,255,255)">Innovation &amp; Creativity</span></span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Judging will be based on Originality and Creativity of the participants, as well as the Persuasiveness of the advertisement.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	The decision of the judges shall be treated as final and binding. The organizers reserve the rights to change any or all of the above rules as they deem fit. Change in rules, if any will be highlighted on the website and notified to the registered participants.</p>\r\n', '', '<p>\r\n	If you have any query, please send an e-mail to <strong>mad@bits-quark.org</strong> or get in touch with any one of us:</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<strong>Shashank Kundurthi<br />\r\n	</strong>+91 9673565723<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space: pre"> </span></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<strong>Aadil Seshadri</strong><br />\r\n	+91 9819572443</p>\r\n', 2, 4),
('4cbc780b-2830-4d1b-996a-05d80a030849', 'Open Showcase', '<p>\r\n	If Charles Darwin were to be in a technocracy, he would definitely modify his famous quote to &quot;<strong>Only the most innovative can survive</strong>&quot;. After all, its innovation that is the driving force in any industry, the element that separates the leaders from the rest of the pack. Innovation is what lets us push the boundaries, explore new vistas, make life easier and more pleasant.<br />\r\n	<br />\r\n	Product Design forms an indispensible arena for any company through which it can expand its horizons, reach out to people and make a mark in these times of cut-throat competition. If Product could be said to represent a Plant then a Project would surely imply its Seed. As budding engineers and young entrepreneurs we see our projects as a reflection of our choices, imagination, skills and thought process and so here is an event which offers you an Open Showcase to exhibit your ideas and skills in the genius of projects based on your disciplines or even a mix of them. It could be you who become the founders of an immensely successful organization and cause tomorrow. So, gear up to plant the enviable seed.<br />\r\n	<br />\r\n	Kindly note, deadline for the event are extended till&nbsp; <strong>January 15, 2011</strong>.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<u><strong>Prizes worth INR 50,000 to be won.</strong></u></p>\r\n', '<p>\r\n	We here at <strong>Open Showcase</strong>, Quark 2011 provide you the stage to showcase the hidden innovative and design skills within you. We present you Open Showcase; an event that promulgates well designed innovative models/projects (working and/or nonworking) relating to any of the following categories:</p>\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<strong>Computer Science and Information Systems / Technology</strong>: Projects based on software applications, applications in real life situations, emerging technologies and innovations from the computing world and fields of information exchange, etc.</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<strong>Electrical, Electronics and Instrumentation</strong>: Projects based on VLSI systems, developments in semiconductor technology, microcontrollers, image and signal processing etc.</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<strong>Chemical and Mechanical</strong>: Projects based on automotive designs, modeling using CAD/CAM, PRO-E and other 3D-Modelling softwares, fluid dynamics etc. Emerging areas of chemical &amp; mechanical engineering like energy crisis, environmental pollution control and innovative industrial applications, etc.</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<strong>Civil and Architecture</strong>: Projects related to designs and construction of sustainable buildings and other structures, handmade models or using modeling softwares like AUTOCAD, ARCHICAD, 3DS MAX, STAAD PRO etc. Green, sustainable design thoughts, better redesign of existing buildings and/ or other structures of importance etc.</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<strong>Pure Sciences</strong>: Projects in Physics, Chemistry, Biology and Mathematics. Research and Projected Applications of the Sciences in day to day life, use of pure sciences in climate change mitigation etc.</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<strong>Management</strong>: Projects carried out in Finance, Economics, Management, Business Studies, and Entrepreneurship etc. Research in subtopics like supply chain management systems, strategic marketing etc.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p>\r\n	*For any information regarding the above mentioned categories please contact the event manager(s).</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<strong><br />\r\n	Eligibility</strong>:<br />\r\n	<br />\r\n	All students with a valid identity card of their respective educational institutes are eligible to participate in the event.<br />\r\n	<b><br />\r\n	</b></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<strong>Certification Policy:</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Certificate of Excellence will be given to all winners.</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Certificates of Participation will be given to all teams that are selected after the abstract submission and are present during QUARK 11.</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Disqualified teams will not be considered for any certificates.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>\r\n	<br />\r\n	<b><br />\r\n	</b><strong>Deadlines</strong>:<br />\r\n	<br />\r\n	Deadline for submission of abstracts is&nbsp; <strong>January 15, 2011</strong>.<br />\r\n	<strong><span class="Apple-style-span" style="font-weight: normal;"><br />\r\n	</span></strong></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<br />\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n', 'openshowcase', '4af9dd7b-f494-45ee-9ab5-1064bb1aea99', '<p>\r\n	<span class="Apple-style-span" style="background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);"><strong>Abstract Submission:</strong></span></p>\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<span class="Apple-style-span" style="background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">&nbsp;Participants should mail their abstracts with the registration number as the subject and the participation category should be clearly mentioned in the body of the mail preferably in &#39;doc&#39; or &#39;PDF&#39; format.</span></li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<span class="Apple-style-span" style="background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">Last Date for submitting the abstracts: 15 January, 2011. An exhibition of the entries selected on the basis of the abstract submitted under Open Showcase event will be held during QUARK 2011. Participants are also required to mention at the beginning of their abstracts if their idea has a prototype / model. A brief idea of how the design would be presented (exhibited) during the exhibition should also be included in the abstracts.</span></li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<span class="Apple-style-span" style="background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">The abstract should be concise and to the point and should not exceed three A4 sheets of text typed with Times New Roman font of size 12 excluding the first sheet containing the title and the last containing the references (if any).</span></li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<span class="Apple-style-span" style="background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">The first sheet should only contain title of the project, team registration number, names of the team members and their respective institutes.</span></li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<span class="Apple-style-span" style="background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">The last sheet, following the abstract, may have a list of references - websites, books, journals and so on which amply support the ideas or solutions implemented/proposed.</span></li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<span class="Apple-style-span" style="background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">The information in the abstract should not be very descriptive or vague. It is recommended that vital aspects of the project that require special focus be mentioned as bold points.</span></li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<span class="Apple-style-span" style="background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">The selected entries will be informed via e-mail and they would have to send replies confirming their participation within two days failing which they will not be allowed to participate.</span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<span class="Apple-style-span" style="background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);"><strong>General Rules:</strong></span></p>\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<span class="Apple-style-span" style="background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">Participants are required to submit a pre-event abstract, in a standard format (as mentioned above) for the screening round. The abstract should be mailed to: open_showcase@bits-quark.org.</span></li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<span class="Apple-style-span" style="background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">&nbsp;Only the participants who are short-listed in the screening round based on judging of the abstracts shall be invited Quark 2011 for the final round.</span></li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<span class="Apple-style-span" style="background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">Qualifying participants will have to make a presentation before a panel of judges explaining the salient points of their idea/innovation.</span></li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<span class="Apple-style-span" style="background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">Teams will be given only one hour prior to the competition to set up their model/design at the venue for judging.</span></li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<span class="Apple-style-span" style="background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">A detailed report in support of the design and highlighting the important aspects should also be brought. The report will be considered for judging.</span></li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<span class="Apple-style-span" style="background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">Participants should list their hardware, software and other requirements (if required) needed at the time of competition along with the abstract for the screening round.</span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n', '<p>\r\n	<span class="Apple-style-span" style="background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">The participant will be judged on the following criteria:</span></p>\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<span class="Apple-style-span" style="background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">Innovation</span></li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<span class="Apple-style-span" style="background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">Feasibility and Sustainability</span></li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<span class="Apple-style-span" style="background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">Cost Effectiveness</span></li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<span class="Apple-style-span" style="background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">Marketability and Manufacturability</span></li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<span class="Apple-style-span" style="background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">Presentation</span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p>\r\n	<span class="Apple-style-span" style="background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">The decision of the judges shall be treated as final and binding on all. The organizers reserve the rights to change any or all of the above rules as they deem fit. Change in rules, if any will be highlighted on the website and notified to the registered participants.</span></p>\r\n', '', '<div>\r\n	If you have any query, please send an e-mail to <strong>open_showcase@bits-quark.org</strong> or get in touch with any one of us:</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	<strong>Mohit Jain</strong><br />\r\n	+91 9049268790</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	<strong>Tanuj Murlidhar Nandurkar</strong><br />\r\n	+91 9096213851</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	<strong>Anuja Niranjan Sahasrabudhe<br />\r\n	</strong>+91 7709790830</div>\r\n', 1, 3),
('4cbc783f-0404-4928-adc6-05d80a030849', 'Spell Bee', '<p>\r\n	The Quark 2011 team brings you an event that eclipses all boundaries of streams and years and ensures an entertaining and enriching experience for one and all.&nbsp; Spelling in English can often be a daunting task because of differences in the apparent pronunciation and the spelling itself, often making it quite an unnerving activity for many.&nbsp; In this event, your goal is very simple - gain as many points as you can in different rounds of a spelling activity. With no prior knowledge, experience or training required and absolutely no demands on participants in terms of logistics, this in an event that is bound to amaze you like very few others.</p>\r\n', '<p>\r\n	<strong>On Campus Rounds</strong> :</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<strong><br />\r\n	Round&nbsp; 1</strong> (Elimination Round)</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n		&nbsp;A written round where the teams will be given a set of 10 words (some marked &#39;<strong>*</strong>&#39; and &#39;<strong>**</strong>&#39; ) and they will have to write the spellings on a sheet of paper.</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Top seven teams will be selected for further rounds.</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		In case of any ties the star marked words will be given priority as per their rating.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>\r\n	<strong>Round&nbsp; 2</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n		One word&nbsp; will be given (pronounced by the judge )&nbsp; to all the teams and the teams will have to write down the answer in 15 seconds and&nbsp; one member of each team will have to recite their answer on stage.</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		One of the participants from each team will be called upon to pick two chits from a draw&nbsp; and select the word he/she wants his/her partner to spell( The word being pronounced by judge/pronouncer)</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		The aim of this round is to shortlist the top 3 teams. (In case of clashes the first word will be given priority)</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		If the no. of qualifiers is more than 3 or less than 3 one of the team members will have&nbsp; to face a word from the judge&nbsp; .</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>\r\n	<strong>&nbsp;Round 3</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n		This consists of a rapid fire round in which a one minute time frame will be given to each team within which they can attempt as many words from a given set as possible.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', 'spellbee', '4af9dd89-e1c0-48e3-9ab7-1064bb1aea99', '<p>\r\n	To be announced soon.</p>\r\n', '', '', '<p>\r\n	If you have any query, please send an e-mail to <strong>spellbee@bits-quark.org</strong> or get in touch with any one of us:</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<strong>Gunveer Gujral<br />\r\n	<span class="Apple-style-span" style="font-weight: normal; ">+91 9545327374</span></strong></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<strong>Dhananjay Deepak Sathe</strong></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<strong><span class="Apple-style-span" style="font-weight: normal; ">+91 9764871950</span></strong></p>', 1, 3),
('4cbc7914-d3a0-4c8c-ac66-05d80a030849', 'E-dorado', '<p>\r\n	The Online Treasure Hunt is back!</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Quark 2010&rsquo;s biggest hit is here again in Quark 2011 to rock all those hunters,but in a new avatar &ndash; BIGGER and BETTER!</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	E-dorado will be a unique &ldquo;race against time&rdquo; game exclusively devoted to testing your agility and numerical skills.&nbsp; A plethora of intriguing questions await you, which, despite being based on basic mathematics, IQ and logical reasoning, are bound to test the efficiency of your grey cells.&nbsp; So gear yourself up for an unrivalled experience this Quark, where time literally flies by.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Online treasure Hunt <strong>E-Dorado</strong> has started. Go play @ <a href="http://www.edorado.in">www.edorado.in</a></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<u><strong>Prizes worth INR 20,000 to be won.</strong></u></p>\r\n', '<p>\r\n	The event consists of questions with varying difficulty.What you can expect here is assortment of various puzzles and direct questions even in the form of multimedia. The subsequent levels will be unlocked as a participant clears the previous levels.In between you will have small quiz sheets of 10-12 questions having time limit and you have to answer all the questions of that sheet correctly to unlock the next level. These sheets will have problems from simple arithmetic and IQ. The questions for the sheets will be generated randomly so as to maintain fair play.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<span _fck_bookmark="1" style="display: none;">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n', 'e_dorado', '4cd9979d-436c-43a1-a830-4ea4bb1aea99', '<p>\r\n	<strong>General Rules:</strong></p>\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Each participant given a unique ID. You are required to log in each time using that ID.</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		You have to answer the questions of each preceding level correctly to unlock the next level, in the process you will be given some hints to answer the questions.</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Each time you login the game starts from where you left.</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		For the quiz sheets you have to answer all questions correctly within the allotted time to move on . There is no limit on the number of trials.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<div>\r\n	&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	The organizers reserve the right to change the rules at any point of time during the event without previous notification.</div>\r\n', '', '', '<p>\r\n	If you have any query, please send an e-mail to <strong><font class="Apple-style-span" color="#000000" face="arial, helvetica, clean, sans-serif"><span class="Apple-style-span" style="border-collapse: collapse; line-height: 15px;">edorado</span></font></strong><span class="Apple-style-span" style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: arial,helvetica,clean,sans-serif; border-collapse: collapse; line-height: 15px;"><span class="Apple-style-span" style="border-collapse: separate; font-family: Arial,Verdana,sans-serif; line-height: normal; color: rgb(34, 34, 34);"><strong>@bits-quark.org</strong> or get in touch with any one of us:</span></span></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<strong>Swapnil Saurav<br />\r\n	</strong>+91 9309271771</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<strong>Aditya Asati<br />\r\n	</strong>+91 9637423454</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<strong>Anurag Singh</strong><br />\r\n	+91 9657293897</p>\r\n', 1, 1);
