style="line-height: 13.5pt;">\r\n	<b><span lang="EN-US" style="color: black;">ELIGIBILITY CRITERIA:</span></b><span lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 11pt; font-family: &quot;Calibri&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;; color: black;">Participants are required to carry a valid college-identification proof.</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle" style="text-indent: -18pt;">\r\n	<span lang="EN-US" style="font-family: Symbol;"><span style="">&middot;<span style="font: 7pt &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><span style="color: rgb(255, 0, 0);"><span class="apple-style-span"><span lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 11.5pt; line-height: 115%;">The participants should take a note that they are not allowed to forward or share the links or the pdfs of the case study with anyone else and it would be a violation</span></span></span><span lang="EN-US">. Anyone found doing so will be immediately disqualified.</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle" style="text-indent: -18pt;">\r\n	<span lang="EN-US" style="font-family: Symbol;"><span style="">&middot;<span style="font: 7pt &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><span style="color: rgb(255, 0, 0);"><span class="apple-style-span"><span lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 11.5pt; line-height: 115%;">The participants should use the link only once to download the case study</span></span><span lang="EN-US">.</span></span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle" style="text-indent: -18pt;">\r\n	<span lang="EN-US" style="font-family: Symbol;"><span style="">&middot;<span style="font: 7pt &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><span lang="EN-US">The team name, college name, members and contact details should be mentioned on the cover page of the report.</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle" style="text-indent: -18pt; line-height: 150%;">\r\n	<span lang="EN-US" style="font-family: Symbol;"><span style="">&middot;<span style="font: 7pt &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><span lang="EN-US">Report Specifications:</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle" style="margin-left: 72pt; text-indent: -18pt;">\r\n	<span lang="EN-US" style="font-family: Wingdings;"><span style="">&Oslash;<span style="font: 7pt &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;">&nbsp; </span></span></span><span lang="EN-US">Page limit is 5.</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle" style="margin-left: 72pt; text-indent: -18pt;">\r\n	<span lang="EN-US" style="font-family: Wingdings;"><span style="">&Oslash;<span style="font: 7pt &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;">&nbsp; </span></span></span><span lang="EN-US">Font type &ndash; Times New Roman ; Font size &ndash; 12</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle" style="margin-left: 72pt; text-indent: -18pt;">\r\n	<span lang="EN-US" style="font-family: Wingdings;"><span style="">&Oslash;<span style="font: 7pt &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;">&nbsp; </span></span></span><span lang="EN-US">Line spacing should be 1.5</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle" style="margin-left: 72pt; text-indent: -18pt;">\r\n	<span lang="EN-US" style="font-family: Wingdings;"><span style="">&Oslash;<span style="font: 7pt &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;">&nbsp; </span></span></span><span lang="EN-US">Text should be left-aligned</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle" style="text-indent: -18pt;">\r\n	<span lang="EN-US" style="font-family: Symbol;"><span style="">&middot;<span style="font: 7pt &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><span lang="EN-US">The report should be submitted in the MS Word or PDF zip file format.</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle" style="text-indent: -18pt;">\r\n	<span lang="EN-US" style="font-family: Symbol;"><span style="">&middot;<span style="font: 7pt &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><span lang="EN-US">Plagiarism is strictly discouraged and is grounds for rejection.</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle" style="text-indent: -18pt;">\r\n	<span lang="EN-US" style="font-family: Symbol;"><span style="">&middot;<span style="font: 7pt &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><span class="apple-style-span"><span lang="EN-US" style="color: black;">The shortlisted candidates will be called to give a presentation of their</span></span><span lang="EN-US" style="color: black;"> <span class="apple-style-span">solutions before the panel of judges during QUARK.</span></span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoListParagraphCxSpLast" style="text-indent: -18pt;">\r\n	<span lang="EN-US" style="font-family: Symbol;"><span style="">&middot;<span style="font: 7pt &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><span lang="EN-US">The decision of the judges is final and binding.</span></p>\r\n', '<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n		There will be eliminations after the online round.</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Rules for each round will be conveyed to the participants before each round.</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Participants will be judged on the basis of their business acumen and on how sustainable and innovative their solution is.</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		The decision of the judges will be final and irrevocable.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', '', '<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-left: 18pt;">\r\n	<span style="font-size: 12px;">In case of any query, please send an email to <strong>intellect@bits-quark.org</strong> or get in touch with any of us:</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-left: 18pt;">\r\n	<b>Jay Khattar</b></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-left: 18pt;">\r\n	+91 93702 53070</p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-left: 18pt;">\r\n	<b>Taijas &nbsp;Malpani</b></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-left: 18pt;">\r\n	+91 98600 02815</p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-left: 18pt;">\r\n	<b>Aditya Dadu</b></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-left: 18pt;">\r\n	+91 96659 10025</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-left: 18pt; display: inline ! important;">\r\n	<b><b><b><br />\r\n	</b></b></b></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<b><b><b><br />\r\n	</b></b><br />\r\n	</b></p>\r\n<div>\r\n	<b><br />\r\n	</b></div>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<span style="font-size: 12px;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></p>\r\n', 2, 4);
INSERT INTO `events` (`id`, `name`, `intro`, `details`, `route`, `category_id`, `rules`, `judging_criteria`, `additional_info`, `contact`, `min_participants`, `max_participants`) VALUES
('4cbc79c1-f92c-40d6-a593-05d80a030849', 'QuEST', '<p>\r\n	In a fast changing world, constant reinvention of strategies is the need of the hour. QuEST 2011 takes you on a journey exploring the entrepreneur in you through a multidimensional world that tests your skills in reaching out to almost all strata of society. &nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<u><strong>Prizes worth INR 22,000 to be won.</strong></u></p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;">\r\n	<img alt="" height="102" src="http://www.bits-quark.org/portal/img/uploads/NBILogo.jpg " width="200" /></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<strong>QuEST</strong> - Quark Entrepreneurial Skills Test is planned to test the participants&rsquo; marketing skills, business sense, quick thinking, decision-making, crisis management and teamwork.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<span class="Apple-style-span" style="font-size: 14px; font-weight: bold;">Event Specifications:</span></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<span class="Apple-style-span" style="font-weight: bold;"><strong>Round 1: Bottom of the Pyramid</strong></span></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	The bottom of the pyramid is the largest, but poorest socio-economic group. In global terms, this is the 2.5 billion people who live on less than $2.50 per day. The phrase &ldquo;bottom of the pyramid&rdquo; is used in particular by people developing new models of doing business that deliberately target that demographic, often using new technology. The same goes for a marketing strategy; until and unless it reaches the masses it can&rsquo;t be termed as successful. The model assumes enhanced importance for a country like ours. Here we ask you to design an interface for a product or service of your choice targeting the Indian BOP so that projects can reach from the tables of the corporate CEO&rsquo;s to the grass root level of the Indian consumer strata.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	You are required to submit an online abstract for such an interface which can cover any product/service (Abstracts should be in about 500 words)to the id quest@bits-quark.org.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Last date for submission of Round 1 entry :<span style="font-weight: bold;">2</span><strong>5th January</strong></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<span class="Apple-style-span" style="font-weight: bold;">Round 2: Fun on the Run:</span></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Do you think that crisis management and decision making have become too boring?? Not anymore!!! Build your automobile empire one block at a time. Bid on the source or seal deals to make and sell your own set of wheels on the virtual market. Invest in the future and build up your own Business Empire. The round gives a taste of the real corporate world, thus your entrepreneurial skills would be put to test.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<span class="Apple-style-span" style="font-weight: bold;">Round 3: Rage in Riviera:</span></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Think you can create a niche for yourself like Giorgio Armani?? Believe that you can make your mark as the next Henry Ford. Think again, for this round happens to be Quest&rsquo;s Riviera. The aim will be to design a dedicated service (and not product) for the top of the line tourists visiting Goa. A detailed presentation on the same will be given in front of the judges who will include eminent people from the same background.</p>\r\n<h4>\r\n	Showdown:</h4>\r\n<p>\r\n	In this round the participants will also get a chance to test the wits of their opponents in a showdown for displaying the supremacy of their idea though a barrage of questions thrown by both the judges and the opponents.&nbsp;</p>\r\n', 'quest', '4af9bedd-cd34-47ed-8dcc-1064bb1aea99', '<h3>\r\n	<strong>Eligibility Criteria:</strong></h3>\r\n<p>\r\n	Participants are required to carry a valid college-identification proof.</p>\r\n', '<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n		There will be eliminations after each round.</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Rules for each round will be conveyed to the participants before each round.</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Judges decision is irrevocable.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', '', '<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	If you have any query, please send an e-mail to <strong>quest@bits-quark.org</strong>, or get in touch with any one of us:</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<strong>Piyush Singh<br />\r\n	<span class="Apple-style-span" style="font-weight: normal;">+91 9921447134</span></strong></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<strong>Amit Raj<br />\r\n	</strong>+91 9561935626</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<strong>Tushar Mandar<br />\r\n	</strong>+91 9850574593</p>\r\n', 1, 2),
('4cbc79f6-8df4-4171-a167-05d80a030849', 'Wall Street Revolution', '<p>\r\n	It is said that stock trading is an art in itself. &nbsp;The stock market is a virtual battleground for dreams - some of them are realised magnificently, while some bite the bitter dust. The Wall Street Revolution provides a virtualization of the same, albeit on a smaller scale. It aims at acquainting the participants with the nuances of the stock markets by providing a simulation of the real-world stock trading scenario.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	A quick, analytical mind, the ability to think on one&#39;s feet and rapid reflexes are the only prerequisites to winning the Wall Street Revolution.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<u><strong>Prizes worth INR 10,000 to be won.</strong></u></p>\r\n', '<h4>\r\n	Event Specifications:</h4>\r\n<p>\r\n	Each team will be given an individual console, where they can trade in real-time on fictitious stocks with fictitious currency. The value of each stock fluctuates in accordance with news snippets that are regularly flashed, as well as the company history. Transactions are carried out as per the availability of the stocks; i.e. one can buy a stock only when someone else is ready to sell that stock at the agreed value. The procedure for trading is similar to that followed in a real stock exchange, but on a simplified level.</p>\r\n', 'wsr', '4af9bedd-cd34-47ed-8dcc-1064bb1aea99', '<p>\r\n	<strong>Eligibility Criteria</strong>: A valid college identification card.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<strong>General Rules:</strong></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	1. A student can represent only one team and cannot be a part of more than one team</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	2. Any number of teams can participate from the same college</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	3. A team can have members from different colleges.</p>\r\n', '<p>\r\n	The participant with the maximum portfolio value at the end of the session, will be declared the winner.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Watch out for updates regarding explicit details of the event!</p>\r\n', '<p>\r\n	The procedure for trading is similar to that followed in a real stock exchange, but on a simplified level.</p>\r\n', '<h4>\r\n	Event Manager:</h4>\r\n<p>\r\n	If you have any query, please send an e-mail to <strong>wallstreet@bits-quark.org</strong> or get in touch with :</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<strong>Ameya Karambelkar<br />\r\n	</strong>+91 98507 48946</p>\r\n', 1, 2),
('4cbc7a4a-afc4-43cd-9d01-05d80a030849', 'Binary Pirates', '<p>\r\n	Put on your Hacking Hats, as it is time to distinguish the best from the rest. Quark 2011 brings you Binary Pirates.<br />\r\n	<br />\r\n	Get ready to put those hacking skills to the test. Go head to head against the best hackers from all over the country.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<strong>Binary Pirates Sample Online Round has started. </strong>Log on to<strong> www.bits-quark.org/binarypirates to play .</strong> (You need to register again on the site)</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<u><strong>Prizes worth INR 10,000 to be won.</strong></u></p>\r\n', '<p>\r\n	Binary Pirates will be a fully online event and will commence from first week of&nbsp; February 2011. Every level will have a &#39;flag&#39; which the participants will have to capture and submit to move on to the next level.To capture the flag you have to decrypt encrypted messages, hijack authenticated sessions, analyze cookies to gain administrator access, inject SQL strings to gain insight about the database structures, or use brute force to hack into password protected files etc. The hacker to reach the top first will be the winner.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<strong>Event Execution</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Binary Pirates will be a fully online event. Eligible participants will need to register online prior to the commencement of the event.</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		The participants will be faced with a problem in each level. They will need to retrieve a flag (which is a string) and submit the flag to proceed to the next level.</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		The participants may use the internet (or any other source) extensively to gather whatever information they might need to crack the problem.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>\r\n	<strong>Rounds</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n		There will be only be one online round, which will start from first week of february and will go on for 3 days</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		A sample online round will be put up on 25th January 2011. This round will not be evaluative, the only motive of this round is for the participants to get a general idea about the event format and get used to the web application used for the event.</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		The links for the rounds will be made available as and when the organizers see fit.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>\r\n	<strong>Sample Round</strong></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	The sample round will be made online on 25th January 2011.</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n		This round will consist of 5 questions only.</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		There will be no evaluation based on this round.</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		The purpose of this round is to familiarize the participants with the format of the event. Feedback on the web application used for the event is welcome.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>\r\n	<strong>Final Round</strong></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	The final round will be made available online from first week of February 2011. This round will go on for 3 days.</p>\r\n', 'bp', '4af9dd24-57f4-4ba4-aad7-1064bb1aea99', '<p>\r\n	There are NO RULES!<br />\r\n	<br />\r\n	Thats right, this is the only rule for Binary Pirates.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Think outside the box, do whatever you must to capture the flag and race to the next level! The event will test your understanding of networking principles and web technologies as well as your ability to bend them to suit your needs. Basic web development experience and knowledge about common hacks will be an added advantage.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Round will contain 40 problems with ranging difficulty</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Only five problems will be made available to the participants at a time.</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		The participants will have to solve one of those five problems to unlock the next problem.</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Hints for particular problems will be provided by the moderators in due course of time during the Final Online Round.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', '<p>\r\n	The teams will be evaluated based on the following criteria prioritized in that order:</p>\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Time required for completion of the event.</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Number of problems solved.</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		The number of advanced (latter) problem hacked.</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		If it&#39;s a tie with respect to the above two criteria, participants will be ranked on the basis of who reached that level first.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n', '<p>\r\n	Here are some custom made tutorials for the event which will give you&nbsp; basic info of some of the fields which will be covered in the Problem Statement. <a href="http://www.bits-quark.org/portal/files/BinaryPiratesTutorials.pdf">Click here to download them.</a></p>\r\n', '<p>\r\n	If you have any query, please send an e-mail to <strong>binarypirates@bits-quark.org</strong>, or get in touch with any one of us:</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<strong>Smarth Behl</strong><br />\r\n	+91 9552518876</p>\r\n', 1, 1),
('4cbc7a7d-579c-43dc-b2be-05d80a030849', 'Geek N Latin', '<p>\r\n	<strong>Code Obfuscation</strong><br />\r\n	<br />\r\n	Bored of well laid out indentations or programs which are too easy for your friends to understand? Feel like doing something to it that could boggle anyone&#39;s mind who tries to reverse engineer its meaning. Then come and join &quot;GEEK N LATIN&quot; and cook us a program that only you can digest. Delude your friends and the so called code cheaters with the weird and wavy style, or algorithms which are way out of the normal sane norms, the choice is yours. We just want your program to run and the more incomprehensible you make it the more points you will be awarded.<br />\r\n	<br />\r\n	<strong>Esoteric languages</strong><br />\r\n	<br />\r\n	If you think the high level languages are pretty low by your standards, say them adieu and enter the world of Brainfuck and Whirl. A world where keywords have no meaning, functions are non-existent and where operators rule the roost. Designed for a select few who are looking for innovative ways to solve a problem and are not easily bogged down by the ways to accomplish it.<br />\r\n	<br />\r\n	If the above lines interest you, come and be a part of &quot;GEEK N LATIN&quot;, and test your algorithms with the best brains around, where more than your technical knowledge, your problem solving aptitude will take you far.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<strong><a href="http://www.bits-quark.org/portal/files/GeekNLatin-softwares.rar">Click here to download</a> important softwares required to solve the problems.<br />\r\n	</strong></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Check out the <strong>details</strong> and <strong>rules</strong> sections for important info.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<u><strong>Prizes worth INR 15,000 to be won.</strong></u></p>\r\n', '<p>\r\n	The event consists of basically two fun sections of modern day programming, viz.- Code obfuscation and Esoteric languages.<br />\r\n	<br />\r\n	Code obfuscation or the act of deliberately making a code difficult to understand is an important means of security through obscurity. The event consists of rounds which test the programmer&#39;s tactics to obfuscate his/her code and also to deobfuscate the code samples given. <br />\r\n	<br />\r\n	Esoteric languages are very popular among the hackers and programmers who want to test the boundaries of&nbsp; programming language design. We have included one of the most popular esoteric language out there- Brainfuck along with another one- Whirl to see if the the programmers can match the challenges offered by these languages and&nbsp; then write programs in them to achieve the solution they want.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<strong>Pre-Quark Round Description</strong><br />\r\n	<br />\r\n	The rounds consist of three sub-divisions:<br />\r\n	<br />\r\n	There will be two Pre-Quark rounds having parallel entries as well as few cumulative ones. Both rounds will be similar in structure and difficulty and will consist of four sections each, with marks to each question. You have to score as high as you can if you want to adavnce to the finals.</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Error removal from Obfuscated C-code - In this type, obfuscated C Code will be given along with some errors and the expected output will also be told. So the task would be to reverse engineer the code; crack the logic and then correct the error.</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		A set of problem statements will be given and the participants have to submit the obfuscated code in C/C++. Step by step explanation of the methods used for obfuscation must be provided.</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Brainfuck questions - A set of problem statements will be given and the participants will have to submit the bf code of the same.</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Whirl questions -&nbsp; A few problems will be given and the code has to be submitted in Whirl language.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>\r\n	<br />\r\n	<strong>Finals</strong><br />\r\n	<br />\r\n	In the finals, only Brainfuck and Whirl questions would be provided to the participants and they have to submit the answers as early as possible. The problems would be of considerably higher difficulty level than the preliminary rounds. The team submitting the code at the earliest wins the Event!<br />\r\n	<br />\r\n	But the event doesn&rsquo;t end so simply!! There is a twist as well. The next team finishing in the interval of 10mins will go to the tie-breaker round. So let us say that Team1 finished their solutions &ndash; now if Team2 finishes in less than 10 mins of that then they both go for the tie-breaker round for the 1st and 2nd positions. Otherwise Team1 is the winner and then the 2nd and 3rd positions simply go to the next two teams who finish the solutions in that order. So when someone finishes their solutions, you better hurry up!<br />\r\n	<br />\r\n	<strong>Tie-Breaker</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n		In the tie-breaker round, only the top two teams (the first team and the second team which submits in the next 10mins of the first team) compete against each other.</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Both the teams will be provided with an obfuscated code which they have to reverse engineer and provide us with the output. The team which finishes first becomes the winner of Geek N Latin!</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		If both team fail then the 3rd team will also be given a chance and they will emerge the winner if they get the output right, failing which the intial order before the tie-breaker will prevail.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', 'GeeknLatin', '4af9dd24-57f4-4ba4-aad7-1064bb1aea99', '<p>\r\n	<strong>For preliminary online rounds<br />\r\n	</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n		A team can participate in either of the two or even both online rounds.</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		The selection of the teams from the Online rounds would be as follows:\r\n		<ul>\r\n			<li>\r\n				The top 4 teams from Online Round 1 will be automatically selected for the On-Campus finals during quark.</li>\r\n			<li>\r\n				Similarly the top 4 teams from Online Round 2 will be selected for the finals. In effect the two online rounds thus act as parallel means to get into the finals.</li>\r\n			<li>\r\n				Top 2 consistent performers based on their cumulative points in the online rounds will also advance to the finals.</li>\r\n			<li>\r\n				In addition to it we have 2 wild card entries in the campus during quark. So even if you don&#39;t make the cut in the first two rounds, solve us a challenging brainfuck problem on campus during quark and you can compete with the other 10 contestants in the big finals.</li>\r\n		</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		The solutions to both the rounds must be submitted within the deadlines given for the particular rounds.The dates and time will be declared in due time.</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		You are allowed to send more than one entry for the rounds in an overall zipped folder. We will only consider the last folder you send.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>\r\n	<br />\r\n	<strong>For the on-campus finals</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n		A separate computer system will be provided to each of the 12 finalist team for the finals.</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		The softwares on each will include a bf interpreter, whirl machine, C/C++ compiler and a text editor. The exact list will be put up before the finals take place. No other softwares or even onternet can be used during the event.<br />\r\n		&nbsp;</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', '<p>\r\n	<strong>Online Elimination Rounds</strong></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	The C obfuscation and Brainfuck/Whirl programs will be checked for their output. The best obfuscated code will get most number of points. Further, the obfuscated codes will be judged on the following basis:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Number and complexity of steps used which are relevant obfuscating transformations. Please note that using only spaces to delude a reader doesn&#39;t count for a good obfuscation.Try working on the algorithms.</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Size of the program. (Maximum acceptable size is 3072 bytes. Programs of size greater than this value will not be accepted)</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Execution time.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>\r\n	<strong>Special Note</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n		The decision of the judges shall be treated as final and binding on all.</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		The organizers reserve the rights to change any or all of the above rules as they deem fit. Changes in the rules, if any will be highlighted on the website and notified to the registered participants.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', '<p>\r\n	Here are some custom made tutorials for the event which will give you&nbsp; basic info of some of the fields which will be covered in the Problem Statement. <a href="http://www.bits-quark.org/portal/files/GeeknLatinResources.rar ">Click here to download them.</a></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	The following links can be helpful for participants:</p>\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n		http://www.ioccc.org/</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Obfuscated_code</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Brainfuck</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		http://www.4mhz.de/bfdev.html</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Geek n latin tutorials Tutorials:</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Softwares:<br />\r\n		<ol>\r\n			<li>\r\n				An online bf interpreter-you can practice here too-http://www.iwriteiam.nl/Ha_bf_online.html</li>\r\n			<li>\r\n				Download the Whirl machine from here,it greatly helps in programming compared to other interpreters available- http://www.bigzaphod.org/whirl/Whirl-1.01.swf</li>\r\n			<li>\r\n				<a href="http://www.bits-quark.org/portal/files/GeekNLatin-softwares.rar">Click Here to Download</a> all the softwares which will be required for you to participate<br />\r\n				&nbsp;</li>\r\n		</ol>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n', '<p>\r\n	If you have any query, please send an e-mail to <strong>geeknlatin@bits-quark.org</strong>&nbsp;or get in touch with any one of us:</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<strong>Shekhar Suman</strong>&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n	+91 8805140330&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<br />\r\n	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<br />\r\n	<strong>Vikas Goel<br />\r\n	</strong>+91 9049269032<br />\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n', 1, 2),
('4cbc7ab5-f7fc-454c-8fbb-05d80a030849', 'PRO''g''RAMMERS', '<p>\r\n	Don&rsquo;t you get sleep until you get the code right? Does your table have coffee stains all over it? Then yes! You are suffering from coding insomnia. The fast spreading, rapidly becoming common deficiency among the PRO&#39;g&#39;RAMMERS. We invite all the victims to spend sleepless nights . Plunge into the sea of codes, dive with the waves of algorithms. Here is the opportunity to put your skills to test. Compete with programmers across the nation and get to know where you stand.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Round 1 Results : <a href="http://www.bits-quark.org/portal/files/ProgrammersRound1Result.pdf ">Click here to download&nbsp;</a></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<strong>2nd Set of Preliminary Round:</strong>&nbsp;<a href="http://www.bits-quark.org/portal/files/programmers_firstround_set2.zip " target="_self">Click here</a>&nbsp;to download the problem statement.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	(Those who participated in 1st Set need not submit again)</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<u><strong>Prizes worth INR 15,000 to be won.</strong></u></p>\r\n', '<p>\r\n	Any one with basic knowledge of C or Java can participate</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	The participants will have to choose either C or Java for the entire event.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	The Event consists of 3 rounds<br />\r\n	<br />\r\n	<strong>PRELIMINARY ROUND</strong> (pre quark event)</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n		This is an online round.</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		It consists of 2 sets of questions: one for C and the other for Java.</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Participants will have to choose only ONE of them.</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		The questions will test their basic knowledge and concepts in programming.</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		For those of you who are PROest of the PRO&#39;s, we give you a chance to score bonus points</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		2 bonus questions will be given to those who finish 18 questions (out of 20) correctly.</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<strong>Online Round:</strong>&nbsp;<a href="http://www.bits-quark.org/portal/files/QUARK2011_PROgRAMMERS1.zip" target="_self">Click here</a>&nbsp;to download the problem statement.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>\r\n	<strong>INTERMEDIATE ROUND</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n		This is an on-campus round. It basically tests your skills at debugging.</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		&nbsp;Code will be given with logical as well as compiling errors in them.</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		The participants will have to debug the code and get the desired output.</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		They will be provided with compilers.</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Time will be the judging criteria.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>\r\n	<strong>ELITE ROUND</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n		This is the final round.</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		The participants will be asked to write the code for a given question in writing (not in the compiler)</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		They will be given compiler only twice&nbsp;&nbsp; /*with specified time limit */ &nbsp;to verify their code and correct compiling errors.</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		&nbsp;If they desire to use the compiler more than twice, points will be deducted.</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Time and number of errors will be the judging criteria.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>\r\n	The person with the highest score after the three rounds will be the winner.</p>\r\n', 'Pro', '4af9dd24-57f4-4ba4-aad7-1064bb1aea99', '<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Individual participation. i.e. no groups are allowed.</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Starting with the preliminary round, each participant should select one language, either C or Java and continue with that throughout the event.</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		In the intermediate and elite rounds, the participants can carry the print-out of the resource material provided by us and any ONE book of their choice.</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		For the preliminary round, 2 sets of questions will be released in an interval of 10 days. Once a set is released, the answers should be mailed back within 1 week.</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		There will be no internet access during the intermediate and elite rounds.</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		In the intermediate round, the participants will be provided with the compiler. They can choose either Turbo C or the GCC compiler.</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		In the elite round, the participants have to write the code in notepad/wordpad/gedit(for Linux).Compiler will be provided for a maximum of 2 times to check their code and remove compilation errors. If they wish to use the compiler more than 2 times, points will be deducted.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', '<p>\r\n	In the preliminary round, each question may have different marking scheme (which will be quite transparent) based on the type of question. Participants answering more than 18 questions out of 20 correctly will be given 2 bonus questions (higher difficulty level and more points if answered correctly).</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	In the intermediate round, if the participants don&rsquo;t get the desired output, based on the number of errors corrected by the participant he/she will be judged. If more than one person gets the output, the one who solves it faster will be getting more points.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	In the elite round, if the participants don&rsquo;t get the output, then their logic will be checked (nothing to do with points) and if their approach is right, then their program will be compiled and the one with minimum errors will get more points. If more than one person&nbsp; gets the output, the one who solves it faster will be getting more points.<br />\r\n	<br />\r\n	In the end the one with highest aggregate of points (right from the 1st round) will be the winner.</p>\r\n', '<p>\r\n	Here are some custom made tutorials for the event which will give you&nbsp; basic information of some of the topics which will be covered in the Problem Statement.<a href="http://www.bits-quark.org/portal/files/ProgrammersResources.rar "> Click here to download them.</a></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<strong>Other Resources<br />\r\n	</strong></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<strong>C Resources<br />\r\n	</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n		For Basic knowledge of C the participants can refer the following</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		http://www.exforsys.com/tutorials/c-language.html</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		http://www.its.strath.ac.uk/courses/c/</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>\r\n	Books:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n		&#39;Let Us C&#39; by Yashwant Kanetkar</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		&#39;Programming in ANSI C&#39; by Balagurusamy</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		&#39;Pointers in C&#39; by Yashwant Kanetkar</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		&#39;Problem solving and program design in C&#39; by Elliot Koffman</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>\r\n	<br />\r\n	For Practising questions based on C:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n		http://www.geekinterview.com/quiz/C-Practice-Test.html</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		http://www.indiabix.com/online-test/c-programming-test/</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		http://cquestionbank.blogspot.com/</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Numerical Recipes in C by WILLIAM H.PRESS</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>\r\n	<strong>Java Resources<br />\r\n	</strong></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Internet Resources</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n		http://www.java2s.com/Tutorial/Java/CatalogJava.htm</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		http://download.oracle.com/javase/tutorial/reallybigindex.html</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		http://www.java.happycodings.com/Core_Java/index.html</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		http://www.freejavaguide.com/corejava.htm</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		http://www.roseindia.net/java/beginners/</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		http://java.sun.com/docs/books/tutorial</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>\r\n	Text Books</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n		&nbsp;Core Java (Volume-I) By Cay.S.Horstmann,Gary Cornell</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		&nbsp;Programming with Java, A Primer By Balaguruswamy</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		The Java Programming Language By Ken Arnold, James Gosling, David Holmes</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		&nbsp;Essentials of Java Programming by C.Muthu<br />\r\n		&nbsp;</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>\r\n	( There are plenty of more Books / Internet Resources on C and Java which you can choose on your discretion)</p>\r\n', '<p>\r\n	If you have any query, please send an e-mail to <strong>programmers@bits-quark.org</strong>, or get in touch with any one of us:</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<strong>Sonali Bhadra<br />\r\n	</strong>+91 8055783272</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<strong>Srinivasa Lahiri</strong><br />\r\n	+91 9960533036<br />\r\n	<strong><br />\r\n	Sai Prashant<br />\r\n	<span class="Apple-style-span" style="font-weight: normal;">+91 9657294672</span></strong></p>\r\n', 1, 1),
('4cbc7aea-d500-429f-bf93-05d80a030849', 'RIP Open', '<p>\r\n	Breaking your heads for finding out efficient algorithms?? Fed up of coding huge programs?? Here is RIP OPEN again to refresh your minds and sharpen your analyzing skills.No expert coding skills are required to participate in this event. The event won&rsquo;t check your memory (i.e. you need not know proper codes/syntax of any languages), internet is available through out the event. It will be checking only your analytical and logical skills. Even basic idea of PHP, CSS, HTML, Java scripts, XML etc. would be enough to participate in this event. Infinite ways can be taken to reach the end , all it matters is the final output and nothing else.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<strong>FREEDOM, CREATIVITY, INNOVATION </strong>&ndash; If these words drive you then RIP OPEN is the event for you. Experience the benefits of open source development. A line here, a loop there-it&rsquo;s all about modifying the already written programs and frameworks to create exciting innovations. Contestants need to combine the knowledge of languages like HTML, PHP, MYSQL, Javascript and CSS etc. along with the analytical and logical power. The final output can be obtained by either just modifying one line or by writing 100 lines. It will give the participants an insight into the constantly evolving world of open source where people with innovative ideas get together, share their resources and bring out totally new creations using resources someone else created before them. Internet access throughout the event will ensure ample availability of anything and everything.&nbsp; This event is aimed at creating awareness about web and open source development so that students continue to contribute and amaze the world with their creations.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<strong>Final List of students selected for on-campus round 1<br />\r\n	</strong></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<a href="http://www.bits-quark.org/portal/files/final_list.pdf" target="_blank">Click Here</a> to Download&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<strong>On-Campus rounds on 3rd and 4th february 2011.&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<u><strong>Prizes worth INR 15,000 to be won.</strong></u></p>\r\n', '<p>\r\n	RIP OPEN involves modifying and utilizing already hard coded free/open source resources by using&nbsp; scripting languages like PHP, CSS, HTML, javascript, XML etc. to meet your needs of a new customized code, a better version of the original source. The hard coded free/open source resources will include&nbsp; Open-SourceApplications / prewritten frameworks / open-source libraries, etc.&nbsp; What makes this event different from others is that participants can take help from internet to develop open source codes.<br />\r\n	To modify some code, first the participants need to understand the code given to them. Good analyzing skills and small amount of googling is all that you require. NO hardcore coding skills are required. People with basic knowledge can easily participate. This event will be a great learning experience for anyone.<br />\r\n	<br />\r\n	<strong>How Exactly Will the Event Be Executed?</strong></p>\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Participants will get a folder (Problem Folder) with the following initial resources<br />\r\n		<ul>\r\n			<li>\r\n				Initial codes which would produce some initial output.</li>\r\n			<li>\r\n				A video (wherever required)&nbsp; showing the final desired output required from the participants.</li>\r\n			<li>\r\n				A problem document explaining the question in detail and any other instructions.</li>\r\n			<li>\r\n				Any other resource necessary for that particular question.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;</li>\r\n		</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		We will use the same initial resources (provided to participants) beforehand to generate an output which will be the desired output.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		This desired output will be there with participants in the form of a video (wherever required) or clearly explained in the problem document along with the initial output (also in the video) throughout a round.&nbsp; &nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Participants have to modify the initial codes so that final desired output (as in video/problem document) is obtained.</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Since same output can be obtained in different ways (for e.g. a participant can obtain the same desired output by changing a HTML file while another participant can do it by modifying a CSS file - There will be all kind of files in the folder), the judging criteria is solely based on the final output and not the method used.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Internet access will be provided throughout the round, as the participants can confuse between different syntax amidst different computer languages and we are not checking their memory but their analytical and logical skills. &nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		They can even copy paste some specific codes available freely on internet because the event is all about freely using resources, however the problems will be such that they will require some analyzing and not copy pasting codes from internet.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p>\r\n	<strong>Rounds</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n		2 Online Elimination Phases (open to all).</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		On-Campus Rounds (only for those who get selected in the online phases).\r\n		<ul>\r\n			<li>\r\n				Preliminary Round.</li>\r\n			<li>\r\n				Final Round.</li>\r\n		</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', 'RO', '4af9dd24-57f4-4ba4-aad7-1064bb1aea99', '<p>\r\n	<strong>Online Phases</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n		A team can participate in either of the two or even both online phases.</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Compress and rename the solutions folder with your team id.</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		The selection of the teams from the Online Phases would be as follows:&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		The top teams from Online Phase 1 will be automatically selected for the On-Campus Rounds.</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		The remaining teams will be put on a waiting list who will be decided after the second online round is complete.</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Similarly the top teams from Online Phase 2 will also be automatically selected for the On-Campus Rounds.</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Then a combined waiting list will be made having teams from both the rounds.</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		The remaining teams will be selected based on their standing in the combined waiting list.</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Finally Top 30 teams make it to the on-campus rounds.</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		We will provide links for downloading required softwares like Apache server, phpMyAdmin, MySQL etc. from the internet and other required instructions.</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		The level of problems would be generally easy and would be mostly related to web development languages like PHP-MySQL, Javascript, HTML, CSS, XML, AJAX etc.</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Participants will have to download the Problem folder with all necessary initial codes, video (wherever applicable), Problem Document mentioning problem statement and instructions.</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Any other information which we may feel important will be provided. Only the final output will be evaluated and not the method. Participants will have to send the final codes within a specific time back to organizers through mail. All other instructions will be provided to the participants during the online round.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>\r\n	<strong>Rules for Online Phases</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n		The actual code won&rsquo;t be evaluated, only the output would be evaluated.</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		These will be held in the month of Jan, 2011.</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Further details for these phases will be put up on the website soon and will be communicated to registered participants.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>\r\n	<strong>Preliminary Round</strong></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	The method of the event will remain the same, the participants will be given a problem folder which will have some initial codes, video (wherever applicable), a problem document clearly explaining all the instructions and the problem statements , they will be asked to modify the initial code to make it match the desired output. The problem statement in this level will be a little tough and would be covering wider range of languages, libraries and frameworks to make the round more exciting. Internet facility will be provided throughout the round.<br />\r\n	<br />\r\n	<strong>Rules for Preliminary Round</strong>:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Participants can use the internet, can modify any of the file(s) given or do anything they wish to show us the final output. The actual code won&rsquo;t be evaluated, only the output would be evaluated.</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Each Question will have different marks allotted to it and only on successful completion of the problem, will the team get full marks, in case the output is wrong, there will be no negative marking.</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Hints will be available for every problem, however if a team uses a hint but is still unable to solve the problem, it would lead to a penalty and some marks will deducted from the final score.</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Only top 10 teams will make it to the Final Round.</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Ties, if any, will be resolved by a tie-breaker problem statement.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>\r\n	<strong>Final Round</strong><br />\r\n	<br />\r\n	This is where the teams battle it out to make it to the podium. The tasks will be on different topics of open source coding and the points will vary according to difficulty of the task. Here, participants can be asked to modify open source codes on different platforms or even make another website of their own given some basic components which can be incorporated in their website. They have to understand the dependencies of each component and then include them at right places. The execution of the event will remain same and&nbsp; the participants will be given a problem folder which will have some initial codes, video (wherever applicable), a problem document clearly explaining all the instructions and the problem statements. They will be asked to modify the initial code to make it match the desired output. Internet facility will be provided throughout the round.<br />\r\n	<br />\r\n	<strong>Rules for Final Round</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Participants can use the internet, can modify any of the file(s) given do anything they wish to show us the final output. The actual code won&rsquo;t be evaluated, only the output would be evaluated.</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Each Question will have different marks allotted to it and only on successful completion of the problem, will the team get full marks, in case the output is wrong, negative marking may or may not be there, it will be announced and mentioned in the problem document beforehand.</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		According to points earned by teams in the total time, the top three positions will be decided.</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Ties, if any, will be resolved by a tie-breaker problem statement.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>\r\n	We would provide computers installed with all the required softwares along with internet facility for on-campus rounds.<br />\r\n	<br />\r\n	<strong>Eligibility</strong></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	All students with a valid identity card of their respective educational institutes are eligible to participate in Rip Open in Quark 2011. Participants from different institutions can form a team.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<strong>Special Note</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n		The decision of the judges shall be treated as final and binding on all.</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		The organizers reserve the rights to change any or all of the above rules as they deem fit. Changes in the rules, if any will be highlighted on the website and notified to the registered participants.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', '', '<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Here are some custom made tutorials for the event which will give you&nbsp; basic information of some of the fields which will be covered in the Problem Statements. <a href="http://www.bits-quark.org/portal/files/RIP_OPEN_Resources.rar">Click here to download them.<br />\r\n		</a></li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		The following links can be helpful for participants:<br />\r\n		<ol>\r\n			<li>\r\n				www.w3schools.com</li>\r\n			<li>\r\n				www.sourceforge.net</li>\r\n			<li>\r\n				www.tutorialized.com<br />\r\n				&nbsp;</li>\r\n		</ol>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		We would provide computers installed with all the required softwares along with internet facility for on-campus rounds.<br />\r\n		&nbsp;</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n', '<p>\r\n	If you have any query, please send an e-mail to <strong>ripopen@bits-quark.org</strong>, or get in touch with any one of us:</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<strong>Tushar Handa<br />\r\n	</strong>+91 9049601054<br />\r\n	&nbsp;&nbsp;<br />\r\n	<strong>Harsh Pant<br />\r\n	</strong>+91 9049920418<br />\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n', 1, 3);
INSERT INTO `events` (`id`, `name`, `intro`, `details`, `route`, `category_id`, `rules`, `judging_criteria`, `additional_info`, `contact`, `min_participants`, `max_participants`) VALUES
('4cc21273-06e0-44ae-96a7-439ed1be55ac', 'GanGreen', '<p>\r\n	<strong>1,021 pounds of carbon emission is about average for a household of one person over a year.<br />\r\n	</strong></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<br />\r\n	<strong>Problem Statement</strong>: Use the existing technologies and modify them to design an economical and carbon neutral abode for the coming generations.<br />\r\n	All the technologies used for building the green home must&nbsp; be mentioned properly. The house must consist of a kitchen, a drawing cum dining room, two bed rooms, a toilet and a small lobby and also a small lawn. The total area of plot is 300 sqmt.<br />\r\n	The Total money given to each team for the total construction is 50 Lac INR. Estimate the total cost for construction for your design (a break up is required for each element). <br />\r\n	<strong>Build</strong>:<br />\r\n	* Site design <br />\r\n	* Foundations <br />\r\n	* Walls <br />\r\n	* Insulation <br />\r\n	* Structural moisture control <br />\r\n	* Windows, doors and roofs <br />\r\n	* water and waste management<br />\r\n	* Lighting and daylighting <br />\r\n	* Heating, Ventilating, &amp; Air Conditioning <br />\r\n	* Water heating and plumbing <br />\r\n	* Appliances</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Participants should submit their initial abstract with a brief idea and the technologies they use. Mail your abstracts to <strong>gangreen@bits-quark.org </strong>before <strong>Jan 18th, 2010.</strong></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<u><strong>Prizes worth INR 10,000 to be won.</strong></u></p>\r\n', '<p>\r\n	<strong>A detailed construction plan has to be drawn by the contestants. The effectiveness of the construction techniques and materials used in reducing the carbon emission must be described. </strong></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Modifications can be done in the electrical and mechanical designs of the appliances used to reduce their electricity consumption, heat emission. The reduction in the amount of electricity or LPG consumption and its impact on the environment in terms of heat released or carbon emission must be explained as clearly as possible. Report the reduced electricity and LPG consumption data.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Every effort must be made to reduce the overall carbon emission of the building by absorbing the emitted carbon dioxide (It could be an electrical design or space management).<br />\r\n	The plan must compulsorily contain information such as:<br />\r\n	Electricity consumption(kwh) : &nbsp; __________<br />\r\n	LPG consumption(litres)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; :&nbsp;&nbsp; __________<br />\r\n	A detailed breakup of each element has to be provided.(i.e&nbsp; places where the element is used and the amount of it used, the summation has to be shown and the total amount has to be entered in the text boxes provided.<br />\r\n	<br />\r\n	Give detailed description of the Water management and waste management systems used.<br />\r\n	<strong>Water Management:&nbsp; </strong>The technique or the plan used must be described properly. The results must indicate the net amount of water conserved. The results must show calculations( input-output, mass&nbsp; balance etc.). Figures showing the amount of water used and saved at various processes being carried out in the house should be reported.<br />\r\n	<strong>Waste management:&nbsp;</strong> Recycling techniques of various waste products( paper, sewage etc)must be described thoroughly.&nbsp; Report figures which would show the amount of waste recycled and its impact on the environment( carbon emission or heat or any other kind of pollution).</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<strong>Rounds:</strong></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<strong>Elimination Round</strong>: It will be a <strong>online round</strong>, participants should submit their initial abstract with a brief idea and the technologies they use. Mail your abstracts to <strong>gangreen@bits-quark.org </strong>before <strong>Jan 10th, 2010.</strong></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<strong>Final Round</strong>: Presentaion and softcopy of report submssion on</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Detailed Construction plan.</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Implementation of technologies and methods.</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Detailed costing with break-up of each element.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ol>\r\n</ol>\r\n', 'Gang_Green', '4cd98ece-6040-446e-aaaf-3744bb1aea99', '<p>\r\n	<strong>Eligibility Criteria</strong>: A valid college identification card.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<strong>General Rules:</strong></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	1. A student can represent only one team and cannot be a part of more than one team</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	2. Any number of teams can participate from the same college</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	3. A team can have members from different colleges.</p>\r\n', '<p>\r\n	The plans of the contestants will l be judged according to the LEED (Leadership in Energy &amp; Environmental Design ) norms. The net carbon emission of each plan will be compared. The optimisation applied for cost and materials management will also be considered. <br />\r\n	The costing and carbon emission for each entity will be compared.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<strong>Criteria: </strong>Highest preference will go to a technology ( or idea, maybe related to water management or waste management) with low cost and also reduces the carbon emission of the home substantially.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<br />\r\n	<strong>Basis of elimination:</strong><br />\r\n	The costing and carbon emission for each entity will be compared.<br />\r\n	<strong>Criteria</strong>: Highest preference will go to a technology( or idea) with low cost and low carbon emission.<br />\r\n	During declaration of results a graph of costing vs the carbon emission of a given entity will be displayed.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<strong>Above all the feasibility of the technology will be considered.</strong><br />\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p>\r\n<!--[if gte mso 9]><xml>\r\n <o:OfficeDocumentSettings>\r\n  <o:AllowPNG/>\r\n </o:OfficeDocumentSettings>\r\n</xml><![endif]--><!--[if gte mso 9]><xml>\r\n <w:WordDocument>\r\n  <w:View>Normal</w:View>\r