i-font-family:"Times New Roman";\r\n	mso-bidi-theme-font:minor-bidi;}\r\n</style>\r\n<![endif]--></span></p>\r\n<p class="Style1">\r\n	<span style="font-size: 12px;">For the first round the participants are to make a desiccant wheel that can absorb maximum humidity from atmospheric air. Each team will be provided with a setup containing one hollow chamber with height and width being 1.5 ft and thickness being 8 inches. There will be a dry bulb and wet bulb thermometer in the chamber to measure the amount of moisture. The objective is to absorb as much moisture from the air within the chamber as possible.<br />\r\n	<br />\r\n	The wheel has to be designed by the participants and should not be more than 1 ft in diameter and 3 inches in thickness. The participants also need to have a stand to mount the wheel so that the wheel does not at any time touch the walls of the chamber. The wheel internal design is left to the participants and it is also advised that the participants rotate the wheel at a very slow rpm (not more than 0.3) using a stepper motor for uniform absorption of moisture. No heating element is allowed and participants are to strictly use only desiccating agents as packing inside the wheel. The choice of the desiccant is left to the participants.<br />\r\n	</span></p>\r\n<p class="Style1">\r\n	<span style="font-size: 12px;">The second round is a written round where the participants will be given a problem after the end of the first round and have to come up with a paper for solving the problem. The problem will be based on the first round itself and will be common for all teams. The teams have to come up with a solution and submit the paper the next day.</span></p>\r\n<p class="Style1">\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<span style="font-size: 12px;"><br />\r\n	</span></p>\r\n<p class="Style1">\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal">\r\n	<b><br />\r\n	</b></p>\r\n', 'DESICCANT_WHEEL', '4af9bebf-5bc0-4c6e-9957-1064bb1aea99', '<p>\r\n<!--[if gte mso 9]><xml>\r\n <o: