family:Calibri;\r\n	mso-ascii-theme-font:minor-latin;\r\n	mso-hansi-font-family:Calibri;\r\n	mso-hansi-theme-font:minor-latin;\r\n	mso-bidi-font-family:"Times New Roman";\r\n	mso-bidi-theme-font:minor-bidi;}\r\n</style>\r\n<![endif]--></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<strong>Content of the mail:<br />\r\n	</strong></p>\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Team Name</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Institute Name (If any.)</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Team members&#39; names</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Team members&#39; contact numbers&shy;</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Team members&rsquo; registration numbers</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Team members&#39; email</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<span style="font-family: ''arial'',''sans-serif'';">Choice of vertical (Trash Track, Reach Out or Rural Electrification)</span><span style="font-family: ''arial'',''sans-serif'';"> </span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<span style="font-family: ''arial'',''sans-serif'';">Abstracts should be 06 MS Power Point Slides(</span><span style="font-family: ''arial'',''sans-serif'';">2003 or 2007 format</span><span style="font-family: ''arial'',''sans-serif'';">), the first slide having the <strong>above</strong> details and the rest explaining your idea(<a href="http://www.bits-quark.org/portal/files/TrashTrack_Panacea.ppt "><b><span style="color: rgb(0, 112, 192);">Example</span></b></a></span>)</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<span style="font-family: ''arial'',''sans-serif'';">File size should not exceed 5MB. </span></li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<span style="font-family: ''arial'',''sans-serif'';">Font size should be no less than 12. </span></li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<span style="font-family: ''arial'',''sans-serif'';">The suggested layout of the presentation is (but not restricted to): Your understanding of the problem, approach/methodology, technical analysis and planning.</span></li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<span style="font-family: ''arial'',''sans-serif'';">The file should be named as &quot;TrashTrack_Teamname&quot; or &quot;ReachOut_Teamname&quot; or &quot;RurElect_Teamname&quot;</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class="MsoNoSpacing">\r\n	<span style="font-family: ''arial'',''sans-serif'';">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNoSpacing">\r\n	<span style="font-family: ''arial'',''sans-serif'';">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNoSpacing">\r\n	<strong><span style="font-family: ''arial'',''sans-serif'';">Round 1 || Day 1: Aaveshan</span></strong></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNoSpacing">\r\n	<span style="font-family: ''arial'',''sans-serif'';">Top 3 teams from <b>each</b> vertical will be invited to BITS Goa to give their presentations in front of the judges and panelists. Working models or designed models are expected from each team participating in </span><span style="font-family: ''arial'',''sans-serif'';">Trash Track, Reach Out</span><span style="font-family: ''arial'',''sans-serif'';"> and</span><span style="font-family: ''arial'',''sans-serif'';"> Rural Electrification</span><span style="font-family: ''arial'',''sans-serif'';">. Teams will have to provide a <a href="http://www.bits-quark.org/portal/files/img/uploads/FinalREport.pdf " target="_blank"><b><span style="color: rgb(0, 112, 192);">detailed report</span></b><span style="color: rgb(0, 112, 192);"> </span></a>on their solution. Judges will study the report check feasibility issues and pose questions.</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNoSpacing">\r\n	<span style="font-family: ''arial'',''sans-serif'';">Later on the same day, the qualifying teams will receive a set of questions after the judges study their reports. They will get ONE day&rsquo;s time to prepare answers.</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNoSpacing">\r\n	<span style="font-family: ''arial'',''sans-serif'';">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNoSpacing">\r\n	<strong><span style="font-family: ''arial'',''sans-serif'';">Round 2 || THE FINAL || Day 3: Aarambh</span></strong></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNoSpacing">\r\n	<span style="font-family: ''arial'',''sans-serif'';">The teams will present the answers to the questions put by the judges. And there will be a discussion round where the teams and judges will interact. After considering the feasibility and implementations of the ideas, the results will be announced.</span></p>\r\n', 'Bhagirath', '4cd98ece-6040-446e-aaaf-3744bb1aea99', '<p>\r\n<!--[if gte mso 9]><xml>\r\n <o:DocumentProperties>\r\n  <o:Author>MINAL</o:Author>\r\n  <o:Version>14.00</o:Version>\r\n </o:DocumentProperties>\r\n <o:OfficeDocumentSettings>\r\n  <o:AllowPNG/>\r\n </o:OfficeDocumentSettings>\r\n</xml><![endif]--><!--[if gte mso 9]><xml>\r\n <w:WordDocument>\r\n  <w:View>Normal</w:View>\r\n  <w:Zoom>0</w:Zoom>\r\n  <w:TrackMoves/>\r\n  <w:TrackFormatting/>\r\n  <w:PunctuationKerning/>\r\n  <w:ValidateAgainstSchemas/>\r\n  <w:SaveIfXMLInvalid>false</w:SaveIfXMLInvalid>\r\n  <w:IgnoreMixedContent>false</w:IgnoreMixedContent>\r\n  <w:AlwaysShowPlaceholderText>false</w:AlwaysShowPlaceholderText>\r\n  <w:DoNotPromoteQF/>\r\n  <w:LidThemeOther>EN-US</w:LidThemeOther>\r\n  <w:LidThemeAsian>X-NONE</w:LidThemeAsian>\r\n  <w:LidThemeComplexScript>X-NONE</w:LidThemeComplexScript>\r\n  <w:Compatibility>\r\n   <w:BreakWrappedTables/>\r\n   <w:SnapToGridInCell/>\r\n   <w:WrapTextWithPunct/>\r\n   <w:UseAsianBreakRules/>\r\n   <w:DontGrowAutofit/>\r\n   <w:SplitPgBreakAndParaMark/>\r\n   <w:EnableOpenTypeKerning/>\r\n   <w:DontFlipMirrorIndents/>\r\n   <w:OverrideTableStyleHps/>\r\n  </w:Compatibility>\r\n  <m:mathPr>\r\n   <m:mathFont m:val="Cambria Math"/>\r\n   <m:brkBin m:val="before"/>\r\n   <m:brkBinSub m:val="&#45;-"/>\r\n   <m:smallFrac m:val="off"/>\r\n   <m:dispDef/>\r\n   <m:lMargin m:val="0"/>\r\n   <m:rMargin m:val="0"/>\r\n   <m:defJc m:val="centerGroup"/>\r\n   <m:wrapIndent m:val="1440"/>\r\n   <m:intLim m:val="subSup"/>\r\n   <m:naryLim m:val="undOvr"/>\r\n  </m:mathPr></w:WordDocument>\r\n</xml><![endif]--><!--[if gte mso 9]><xml>\r\n <w:LatentStyles DefLockedState="false" DefUnhideWhenUsed="true"\r\n  DefSemiHidden="true" DefQFormat="false" DefPriority="99"\r\n  LatentStyleCount="267">\r\n  <w:LsdExceptio