('4d243624-c34c-4dc8-83a7-2b9ebb1aea99', 'Creativity Shed', '<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<div style="margin: 0px 0px 0.0001pt; padding: 0px; border-width: 0px; outline-width: 0px; font-size: 12px; background-color: transparent; text-align: justify; line-height: 24px; font-family: Tahoma,Arial,sans-serif;">\r\n	<span class="Apple-style-span" style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51);"><span style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border-width: 0px; outline-width: 0px; font-size: small; background-color: transparent;"><span style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border-width: 0px; outline-width: 0px; font-size: 13px; background-color: transparent; font-family: Arial;"><span style="margin: 0px; padding: 0cm; border: 1pt none windowtext; outline-width: 0px; font-size: 13px; background-color: transparent; line-height: 26px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51);">&quot;Creativity is inventing, experimenting, growing, taking risks, breaking rules, making mistakes, and&nbsp;</span></span></span></span><span class="Apple-style-span" style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Arial; line-height: 26px; font-size: 13px;">having fun.&quot; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;</span><span class="Apple-style-span" style="font-family: Arial,Verdana,sans-serif; line-height: normal;"><font class="Apple-style-span" face="Arial" size="2"><span class="Apple-style-span" style="line-height: 26px;">&nbsp;</span></font><span class="Apple-style-span" style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Arial; font-size: 13px; line-height: 26px;">-- Mary Lou Cook</span></span></div>\r\n<p>\r\n	Can you think out of the box? Can you apply basic sciences to suggest apposite solutions to common predicaments? Because Quark 2011 in association with <a href="http://www.engineersgarage.com"><strong>ENGINEERSGARAGE</strong></a>&nbsp;&nbsp;as our <strong>innovation partners</strong> brings you <strong>CREATIVITY SHED</strong>, a platform for you to display your innovative grey cells to make you conspicuous.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Challenge your aptitude and unleash the unconventional side in you.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;">\r\n	<strong>WINNER OF THE PREVIOUS QUESTIONS ANNOUNCED!!</strong></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;">\r\n	<span style=""><span style="font-size: 18px;"><strong>6th &nbsp;QUESTION UP!!! GO GO GO!!&nbsp;</strong></span></span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;">\r\n	<strong>FIND THE QUESTION IN THE RESOURCE TAB!!&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n', '<p>\r\n	The Problem Statements are based on general daily-life problems which can be solved using basics of science, prudence and rational reasoning along with common sense.&nbsp; <br />\r\n	<br />\r\n	There will be a new question posted every 2 days. The winner will be declared along with the post of the next question.The answers to these questions are to be submitted in a descriptive manner. Most efficient, elegant and feasible solution shall be declared as the winner.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	The questions will be posted on the <a href="http://www.bits-quark.org/portal/creativity_shed"><strong>Quark 2011 website</strong></a>, on <a href="http://www.facebook.com/event.php?eid=142025875854096"><strong>Facebook </strong></a>and on Twitter as well, and the same sources can be used to submit&nbsp; partial answers. Complete answers, however, are to be mailed to <strong>creativity_shed@bits-quark.org</strong>.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	keep looking for special questions in between ,answer them correctly to win hints to the main questions.....</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Check the Rules Section for more details. <br />\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<font class="Apple-style-span" color="#333333" face="Arial" size="2"><span class="Apple-style-span" style="line-height: 26px;"><br />\r\n	</span><span class="Apple-style-span" style="line-height: 26px;"> </span></font></p>\r\n', 'creativity_shed', '4cd9979d-436c-43a1-a830-4ea4bb1aea99', '<p>\r\n	1. A question will be posted every two days starting from <strong>6th January 2011 </strong>at <strong>1 pm</strong><br />\r\n	2. Participants have to mail the answers to <strong>creativity_shed@bits-quark.org, and are supposed to register at the <a href="http://www.bits-quark.org/portal/users/register">Quark website</a> before attempting the question......</strong><br />\r\n	3. Facebook can also be used to answer the questions by answering them as a comment on the Facebook page.<br />\r\n	4. The best answer will be decided after viewing all the entries. (Entries close 3 hours prior to the posting of new question).<br />\r\n	5. The winner&#39;s name will be posted on the site and he/she will be contacted by the Quark 2011 team. <br />\r\n	6. Decisions of the organizing committee will be considered final and are not subject to any changes.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<strong>Modes of Submission of answers</strong><br />\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	1. The answers can be posted on Facebook (not twitter) or mailed to <strong>creativity_shed@gmail.com.</strong><br />\r\n	2. However, only a summary of the answer can be posted on the <a href="http://www.facebook.com/event.php?eid=142025875854096"><strong>Facebook page</strong></a>. The detailed answer has to be mailed at the given E-mail address.<br />\r\n	3. If the summary of the answer exceeds 240 characters (constraint of Facebook), the remaining content should be posted as a comment to the answer.<br />\r\n	4. <strong>Reproducing ideas</strong> used by other applicants will lead to <strong>disqualification</strong> of the applicant.<br />\r\n	5. <strong>Hints</strong> to the problem statements will be posted periodically after every&nbsp; <strong>10 hours</strong>.<br />\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p>\r\n	The winner will be declared along with the post of the next question.<br />\r\n	The answers to these questions are to be submitted in a descriptive manner via a mail to <strong>creativity_shed@bits-quark.org</strong>. Most efficient, elegant and feasible solution shall be declared as the winner.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	The best answer will be decided after viewing all the entries. The number of likes and comments on the facebook page would also be considered for judging.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	(Entries close <strong>3 hours </strong>prior to the posting of new question).&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p>\r\n	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<span class="Apple-style-span" style="font-family: ''lucida grande'', tahoma, verdana, arial, sans-serif; line-height: 14px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); ">prizes sponsored by&nbsp;<a href="http://www.engineersgarage.com/"><strong>engineersgarage</strong></a>&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<strong>QUESTION 6</strong></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<span class="Apple-style-span" style="border-collapse: collapse; font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); ">Molecular Gastronomy has been acquiring steam as a new way to cook food. It involves using the physical and chemical properties of materials to create food which have a different taste and texture than expected. It also involves cooking food in a different way than usual(think cooking sausages by connecting them across a car battery). Can you suggest some other such innovative ways to cook food?</span></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	the summary has to be posted on our <a href="http://www.facebook.com/event.php?eid=142025875854096&amp;index=1"><strong>facebook page</strong></a> where as the complete answers is to be mailed to creativity_shed@bits-quark.org<wbr>. as mentioned before...</wbr></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<wbr>\r\n	<p>\r\n		<wbr></wbr></p>\r\n	<wbr>\r\n	<p>\r\n		<wbr> </wbr></p>\r\n	<wbr><wbr>\r\n	<p>\r\n		<wbr></wbr></p>\r\n	<wbr><wbr><wbr>\r\n	<p>\r\n		<wbr> </wbr></p>\r\n	<wbr><wbr><wbr><wbr>\r\n	<p>\r\n		<wbr></wbr></p>\r\n	<wbr><wbr><wbr><wbr><wbr>\r\n	<p>\r\n		<wbr> </wbr></p>\r\n	<wbr><wbr><wbr><wbr><wbr><wbr>\r\n	<p>\r\n		<wbr></wbr></p>\r\n	<wbr><wbr><wbr><wbr><wbr><wbr><wbr>\r\n	<p>\r\n		<wbr> </wbr></p>\r\n	<wbr><wbr><wbr><wbr><wbr><wbr><wbr><wbr>\r\n	<p>\r\n		<wbr></wbr></p>\r\n	<wbr><wbr><wbr><wbr><wbr><wbr><wbr><wbr><wbr>\r\n	<p>\r\n		<wbr> </wbr></p>\r\n	<wbr><wbr><wbr><wbr><wbr><wbr><wbr><wbr><wbr><