us:<br />\r\n	<br />\r\n	<strong>Pranay Agrawal</strong><br />\r\n	+91 9637423510&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n	<br />\r\n	<strong>Chaitanya Bhatt</strong><br />\r\n	+91 9689808699</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	or log on to:</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<a href="http://www.engineersgarage.com/">http://www.engineersgarage.com</a>&nbsp;or on <a href="http://www.facebook.com/event.php?eid=142025875854096"><strong>FACEBOOK</strong></a></p>\r\n', 1, 1),
('4d2b235a-b080-4257-9402-21e0bb1aea99', 'Indian Sudoku and Puzzle Championships', '<p>\r\n	Quark 2011 brings to you a golden opportunity to qualify for the finals of the Indian Sudoku Championships and the Indian Puzzle Championships conducted by <a href="http://www.logicmastersindia.com/" target="_blank">Logic Masters</a> India and to go ahead and win a chance to represent India at the 6th World Sudoku Championships and the 20th World Puzzle Championships to be held in Hungary!</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<u><strong>Prizes worth INR 8,000 to be won.</strong></u></p>\r\n', '<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p align="justify" class="centerText" style="border-width: 0px; border-style: none; font-family: Arial,sans-serif; font-size: 1em; font-style: inherit; font-weight: inherit; margin: 0px 0px 1em; outline-width: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; text-rendering: optimizelegibility; color: rgb(47, 79, 79);">\r\n	<span class="Apple-style-span" style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Arial,sans-serif;">Sudoku, dubbed as the hottest puzzle sensation since the Rubik&rsquo;s Cube gained worldwide popularity in early 2005. The first World Sudoku championship (WSC) was held in March 2006 in Lucca, Italy. The 6th WSC in 2011 will be held in Hungary. Top rankers at the Indian Sudoku Championship will be eligible to represent India at the 6th World Sudoku Championship to be held in Hungary.</span></p>\r\n<div>\r\n	<p align="justify" class="centerText" style="border-width: 0px; border-style: none; font-family: Arial,sans-serif; font-size: 1em; font-style: inherit; font-weight: inherit; margin: 0px 0px 1em; outline-width: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; text-rendering: optimizelegibility; color: rgb(47, 79, 79);">\r\n		<span class="Apple-style-span" style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Arial,sans-serif;">And while most people would have heard of Sudoku, many have not been introduced to a host of other logic puzzles. These puzzles have been very popular in countries like Japan, the USA and eastern Europe. The first World Puzzle Championship (WPC) was held in 1992 in New York, USA. The 20th WPC in 2011 will be held in Hungary. Top rankers at the Indian Puzzle Championship will be eligible to represent India at the 20<sup style="border-width: 0px; border-style: none; font-family: Arial,sans-serif; font-size: 12px; font-style: inherit; font-weight: inherit; margin: 0px; outline-width: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; text-rendering: optimizelegibility;">th</sup>&nbsp;World Puzzle Championship to be held in Hungary.</span></p>\r\n</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	<span class="Apple-style-span" style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Arial,sans-serif;"><span class="Apple-style-span" style="color: rgb(47, 79, 79);">Quark 2011 in association with Logic Masters India invites you to test your logical skills in the Indian Sudoku Championship &amp; Indian Puzzle Championships and get an opportunity to represent India at the WSC &amp; WPC!</span><br />\r\n	</span></div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	<span class="Apple-style-span" style="color: rgb(47, 79, 79);">All resident Indian nationals, irrespective of age, can participate in ISC and IPC.</span></div>\r\n', 'sudoku', '4af9dd89-e1c0-48e3-9ab7-1064bb1aea99', '<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Now you can directly land into the 2nd round of the event!!!!</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Just solve a Sudoku and grab the opportunity. Last date to send your solved Sudoku&rsquo;s is <strong>28th</strong> January 2011.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	So, hurry!!! Start solving right now&hellip;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<strong>RULES FOR ONLINE ROUND:</strong></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	1) Solve the two Sudokus&rsquo; correctly and mail the answers to sudoku2k11@gmail.com on or before <strong>28th&nbsp;January 2011</strong>.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	2) Participants sending the answers should necessarily register online for the event. Register at <a href="http://www.bits-quark.org/portal/sudoku">http://www.bits-quark.org/portal/sudoku</a> (online registration is free of cost!!)</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	3) Preference will be given for the participants who solve the 2nd Sudoku correctly.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	4) The results will be announced on <strong>31st</strong> January 2011 through Mail/SMS and can be checked on the Quark website.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	5) 15 winners will be announced who will directly enter the second round of the on-campus event to be held on February 4- 5th during QUARK 2011.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	NOTE: Find the document attached below for the questions.</p>\r\n<div>\r\n	<a href="http://www.bits-quark.org/portal/files/ONLINEROUNDQUESTION1.pdf">Online Round Question</a></div>\r\n', '', '', '<p>\r\n	<span class="Apple-style-span" style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Arial; line-height: 18px;">If you have any query, please get in touch with:</span></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<span class="Apple-style-span" style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Arial; line-height: 18px;"><strong>K.N.S Hemanth<br />\r\n	</strong>+91 9637423661</span></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<span class="Apple-style-span" style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); line-height: 18px;"><strong>K.S.N Arjun<br />\r\n	</strong>+91 9960423438</span></p>\r\n', 1, 1),
('4d2dfe0e-c954-429f-93e2-303bbb1aea99', 'CodeJam', '<p>\r\n	If coding is your forte then look no further..Get wired in, unjam your brains, crack the the code and walk away&nbsp;with exciting prices!!!!</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	We bring to you an event which will test your ultimate coding &amp; problem solving skills...so get ready to bring out&nbsp;the coder with in you.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<strong>Final Results :</strong> <a href="http://www.bits-quark.org/portal/files/CodejamResults.pdf ">Click Here to Download</a></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<u><strong>Prizes worth INR 10,000 to be won.</strong></u></p>\r\n', '<p>\r\n	CODEJAM is an online coding event which will test your problem solving skills. Anyone having basic understanding&nbsp;of any programming language can participate. There will be 6 Questions in all with varying difficulties and&nbsp;solution to which have to be uploaded online on our programming partners <span style="font-size: 14px;"><strong>CodeChef</strong></span> website (link will be put up soon). Solutions can be submitted in multiple languages which are - Perl,&nbsp;Python, C++, C &amp; JAVA.</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<strong>Event</strong> will have only <strong>one round</strong> of <strong>6 hours</strong></li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<strong>Questions</strong> will appear on CodeChef website on<strong> 30th January&nbsp;2011 6:00 pm(IST). </strong>The link for website where questions will appear is <a href="http://www.codechef.com/CODEJAM" target="_blank">http://www.codechef.com/CODEJAM</a>. Solutions to the questions can be submitted on same page by logging in with your CodeChef UserID and password <strong>(Please mention your Name &amp; Quark team ID as comments in the solutions</strong>)</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<strong>Solutions</strong> can be <strong>submitted</strong> till<strong> 30th January 2011 11:59 pm(IST)</strong></li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Please refer all the rules before submitting solutions</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', 'codejam', '4cd9979d-436c-43a1-a830-4ea4bb1aea99', '<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n		There are total of 6 problems carrying one point each with detailed explanation and input and output format given.</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Participants should write the code according to the specified input and output only. Failing to do so will lead to&nbsp;wrong solution.</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Only individual participation is allowed.</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Solutions will not be accepted after deadline.</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Each participant need to have one CodeChef username in order to submit solutions online. You can get username by registering on <a href="http://www.codechef.com/user/register/" target="_blank">CodeChef</a> website.</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		You can submit solutions as many times as you&#39;d like, there are no penalties for incorrect submissions. Only the&nbsp;<strong>most optimized solution</strong> will be taken into account.</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Please do not discuss strategy, suggestions or tips in the comments during a live contest. Posting questions&nbsp;clarifying the problem statement is ok.</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		The organizers can add, modify or remove the above mentioned rules. The decision of the organizers will be final.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>\r\n	<span style="font-size: 16px;">IMPORTANT : - Participants should write their CodeJam team ID and their name in comments in starting lines of all the solutions they submit on CodeChef&#39;s website. Failing to do so may lead to disqualification.</span></p>\r\n', '<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n		You will receive one point for solving a problem (passing all test cases - no partial credit).</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Participants are ranked according to the most problems solved. Ties will be broken by the total time for each user in ascending order of time.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', '<p>\r\n	For practicing check out the below mentioned links :-</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<span class="Apple-style-span" style="font-size: 14px; font-weight: bold;">Problems</span></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<a href="http://www.spoj.pl" target="_blank">www.spoj.pl/</a></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<a href="http://www.topcoder.com/tc" target="_blank">www.topcoder.com/tc</a></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<a href="http://www.codechef.com/" target="_blank">www.codechef.com/</a></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>\r\n	Algorithm Tutorials</h3>\r\n<p>\r\n	<a href="http://www.topcoder.com/tc?d1=tutorials&amp;d2=alg_index&amp;module=Static" target="_blank">http://www.topcoder.com/tc?d1=tutorials&amp;d2=alg_index&amp;module=Static</a></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<a href="http://www.algorithmist.com/index.php/Main_Page" target="_blank">http://www.algorithmist.com/index.php/Main_Page</a></p>\r\n', '<p>\r\n	<span class="Apple-style-span" style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Arial; line-height: 18px;">If you have any query, please send an e-mail to&nbsp;<strong>codejam</strong><strong>@bits-quark.org</strong>, or get in touch with any one of us:</span></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<strong>Abhijith Reddy D<br />\r\n	</strong>+91 9730597549</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<strong>Sumit Sharma<br />\r\n	</strong>+91 9049775347</p>\r\n', 1, 1),
('4d439481-2220-4368-94fe-1896bb1aea99', 'Mahindra Scorpio T-shirt Design Contest!', '<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Design a T-shirt here at - <a href="http://www.ilogo.org/design.php?p=662&amp;product_color=_82cac9" target="_blank">http://www.ilogo.org/design.php?p=662&amp;product_color=_82cac9</a> , with the theme being &ndash; &ldquo;<strong>Mahindra Scorpio-India&rsquo;s Iconic SUV</strong>&quot;. &nbsp;Share the URL of your design on Facebook and get your friends to like it!</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	1. After designing, click on <strong>&quot;compete&quot;</strong> to participate in the competition. The designs will appear on the iLogo FB page, <a href="http://www.facebook.com/ilogo.org" target="_blank">http://www.facebook.com/ilogo.org</a> . You can like either the post here or on the page on iLogo with the design.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	2. Participant with most <strong>&quot;likes&quot;</strong> will be the winner.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	3. Do not use more than 6 colours per design.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	The participants getting the top three numbers of likes shall be awarded<u><strong> Prizes worth INR 27000 besides getting their T-shirt printed free of cost by iLOGO.org!</strong></u></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	The contest starts on <strong>30<sup>th</sup> January 10:00am</strong>&nbsp;and ends on <strong>4<sup>th</sup> Feb 5pm.</strong> The winners will be declared on the <strong>5<sup>th</sup> of February.</strong></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>', '', 'scorpio', '4cd9979d-436c-43a1-a830-4ea4bb1aea99', '', '', '', '<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	For any clarifications contact &ndash;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Aniket Pant</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	09637130502</p>\r\n', 1, 1);
