('4ae7405d-d4f4-4a9f-a6a7-1684bb1aea99', 'Welcome', '<p>\r\n	<br />\r\n	Quark is the annual technical and innovation festival held in and by BITS, Pilani - K. K. Birla Goa campus. The objective of Quark is to provide a platform for the best minds in the country to showcase their talent and ingenuity. It aims at motivating students from different disciplines to come together and share the mutual enthusiasm &amp; love in science, technology, management &amp; humanities. It is a platform for the most ingenious minds in the country to showcase their talent.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<strong>Register for accomodation</strong> <a href="http://www.bits-quark.org/portal/hospitality">Click here</a></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<u><em><strong>QUARK Updates</strong></em></u></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<u><em><strong>Guest Lecture Updates:</strong></em></u></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Guest Lecture by ISRO Director Ahmedabad on <a href="/portal/isro_lecture">Satellite Navigation</a>.&nbsp;<br />\r\n		&nbsp;</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>\r\n	<u><em><strong>Workshop Updates: </strong></em></u></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Workshop on Development of Applications on Win7 phone &nbsp;-&nbsp; by Microsoft&nbsp;now on two days, 3rd and 4th February, 2011. To Read more, <a href="http://www.bits-quark.org/portal/windows_phone_7">Click here</a>.</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		The Kit Pictures for the Fuel Cell Development Workshop by GreenAdd+ are now up. To view the pictures, <a href="http://www.bits-quark.org/portal/fuel_cell_greenadd">Click here</a></li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		For the 1st time in India, an Exclusive Workshop on Fractals - By Dr. Jonathan Wolfe, Executive director, Fractal Foundation, New Mexico. To Read more, <a href="http://www.bits-quark.org/portal/fractals_workshop">Click More.</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>\r\n	<strong><u><em>Events Updates</em></u></strong>:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<u><strong>Intellect</strong></u>-<span class="Apple-style-span" style="line-height: 18px; font-family: arial; color: rgb(0,0,0)">Deadline for submitting the solutions to Round 1 is&nbsp;<strong>23<sup>th</sup>&nbsp;January 2011</strong>.</span></li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<u><strong>Quest</strong></u>-<span class="Apple-style-span" style="line-height: 18px; font-family: arial; color: rgb(0,0,0)">Last date for submission of Round 1 entry <span style="font-weight: bold">2</span><strong>5<sup>th</sup> January 2011.</strong></span></li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<u><strong>S.P.A.M</strong></u>-<span><span class="Apple-style-span" style="line-height: 18px; font-family: arial"><span class="Apple-style-span">Last date for submission of entries for the first round is</span><strong><span class="Apple-style-span"> 25<sup>th</sup> January 2011.</span></strong></span></span></li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<u><strong>VeriTas</strong></u>-Veritas deadlines extended to <strong>25<sup>th</sup> January 2011</strong></li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<u><strong>Geek N Latin</strong></u>-<span class="Apple-style-span" style="line-height: 18px; font-family: arial"><strong><span class="Apple-style-span"><span class="Apple-style-span" style="color: rgb(0,0,0); font-weight: normal">Deadline for submitting the solutions to Round 1 is&nbsp;<strong>23<sup>th</sup>&nbsp;January 2011 -17:00hrs</strong></span></span></strong></span></li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<span class="Apple-style-span" style="line-height: 18px; font-family: arial"><span class="Apple-style-span"><span class="Apple-style-span" style="color: rgb(0,0,0); font-weight: normal"><u><strong>RIP Open</strong></u>-Online Round 2 to start from&nbsp;<span class="Apple-style-span" style="font-weight: bold">&nbsp;23<sup>rd</sup> January &nbsp;12 pm</span><em><span class="Apple-style-span" style="font-weight: bold">.</span></em></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<u><strong>Indian Sudoku and Puzzle Championships</strong></u>- Online Round has started for direct entry into Round 2.</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<u><strong>M.A.D</strong></u>- Online Round has started.</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<u><strong>CodeJam</strong></u>-&nbsp;<span class="Apple-style-span" style="line-height: 18px; font-family: arial; color: rgb(0,0,0)"><strong>Questions</strong>&nbsp;will appear on website on<strong>&nbsp;30<sup>th</sup> January&nbsp;2011 6:00 pm(IST) and&nbsp;<span class="Apple-style-span" style="font-weight: normal"><strong>Solutions</strong>&nbsp;can be&nbsp;<strong>submitted</strong>&nbsp;till<strong>&nbsp;30<sup>th </sup>January 2011 11:59 pm(IST).</strong></span></strong></span></li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<u><strong>E-dorado</strong></u>-<span class="Apple-style-span" style="line-height: 18px; font-family: arial; color: rgb(0,0,0)"><strong><span class="Apple-style-span" style="font-weight: normal"><strong><span class="Apple-style-span" style="font-weight: normal">Online Treasure Hunt&nbsp;<strong>E-Dorado</strong>&nbsp;has started. Go play @&nbsp;<a href="http://www.edorado.in/" style="color: rgb(102,102,102)">www.edorado.in</a></span></strong></span></strong></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', 'Other', 'home', ''),
('4ae85a9c-3b9c-40ef-87fe-16840a040761', 'Graviton', '<script type="text/javascript">\r\n\r\nfunction change(x){\r\nif(x=="robotics"){\r\ndocument.getElementById(''robotics'').style.display="block";\r\ndocument.getElementById(''ethical'').style.display="none";\r\n}\r\nif(x=="ethical"){\r\ndocument.getElementById(''ethical'').style.display="block";\r\ndocument.getElementById(''robotics'').style.display="none";\r\n}\r\n}\r\n</script>\r\n<div style="padding: 20px;">\r\n	<p style="padding: 6px;">\r\n		<strong>Graviton</strong> is an off-campus academic innovation disseminating initiative by Quark 2011 aimed at organizing a variety of events including a league of competitions, workshops or talks, with focus on imbibing the spirit of innovation among the student community.</p>\r\n	<p style="padding: 6px;">\r\n		Presently, under this initiative, we are conducting <strong>Graviton Ethical Hacking Workshop Series (GEHWS)</strong>, and <strong>Graviton Robotics Workshop Series (GRWS) </strong>in various cities across India.</p>\r\n	<p style="padding: 6px;">\r\n		For Details :</p>\r\n	<form id="form1">\r\n		<h4>\r\n			Ethical Hacking Workshop <input id="checkpreconfiguredHacking" name="c" onclick="change(''ethical'')" type="radio" value="0" /></h4>\r\n		<h4>\r\n			Robotics Workshop <input id="checkpreconfiguredRobotics" name="c" onclick="change(''robotics'')" type="radio" value="1" /></h4>\r\n	</form>\r\n	<div id="ethical" style="display: none;">\r\n		<p style="padding: 6px;">\r\n			The Ethical Hacking workshop is being organized in association with Kyrion Technologies Pvt. Ltd., an IIT Delhi Alumni Venture.(To Know More Visit: <a href="http://www.kyrion.in/security/home/" style="color: inherit;">http://www.kyrion.in/security/home/</a>)</p>\r\n		<h2 style="padding: 6px;">\r\n			Course Details:</h2>\r\n		<h3 style="padding: 6px;">\r\n			Ethical Hacking Workshop:</h3>\r\n		<p style="padding: 6px;">\r\n			The workshop, designed in association with <strong>Graviton</strong> covers the key concepts of ethical hacking, Trojans, Web Security, Wireless Security and Software Cracking. The course structure is well defined and provides in-depth knowledge on cyber security with the help of live demonstrations.(To Know More: <a href="http://www.bits-quark.org/graviton/graviton_course.pdf" style="color: inherit;">Click Here</a> )</p>\r\n		<p style="padding: 6px;">\r\n			<strong>Schedule: </strong>4<sup>th</sup> and 5<sup>th</sup> September, 2010</p>\r\n		<p style="padding: 6px;">\r\n			<strong>Cost:&nbsp;</strong>900/- per student</p>\r\n		<h2 style="padding: 6px;">\r\n			Other Important Details:</h2>\r\n		<ul>\r\n			Kyrion will provide the following to the students during the workshop:\r\n			<li>\r\n				Ethical Hacking and Information Security software tool kit (worth 750/-) for each student.</li>\r\n			<li>\r\n				Training material &ndash; (E-book) will be given to all students.</li>\r\n			<li>\r\n				Authorized Certification from Kyrion Digital Securities in association with Graviton and Quark 2011.</li>\r\n		</ul>\r\n		<p style="padding: 6px;">\r\n			<span style="margin-left: 20px;"><strong>Registration Closed</strong></span></p>\r\n	</div>\r\n	<div id="robotics" style="display: none;">\r\n		<h2 style="padding: 6px;">\r\n			ROBOTICS WORKSHOP</h2>\r\n		<p style="padding: 6px;">\r\n			The Robotics Workshop is jointly organized by Graviton and Grey Orange Robotics of the Acyut fame. It aims at introducing undergraduate students to the field of robotics, and strengthening. their basics of electronic components and programming, while introducing them to the concepts of microcontroller programming using the Arduino platform. Also the highly advanced seven IR Sensor Line Follower kit enables the students to follow lines of variable thickness and take sharpest possible turns while providing a hands on experience of data packet communication.</p>\r\n		<h2 style="padding: 6px;">\r\n			NO pre-requisites required for the workshop!</h2>\r\n		<a href="http://www.bits-quark.org/graviton/robotics_course_Structure.pdf" style="color: inherit;">Click here to download the course structure and Kit details </a>\r\n		<h2 style="padding: 6px;">\r\n			Schedule:</h2>\r\n		<p style="padding: 6px;">\r\n			1. Bits Pilani Goa: 9th-12th November, 2011 Duration: 18 hours Cost: 7600/- per team</p>\r\n		<h2>\r\n			Highlights of the workshop:</h2>\r\n		<p style="padding: 6px;">\r\n			&nbsp;</p>\r\n		<ol>\r\n			<li>\r\n				Participation in a team of minimum 3 amd maximum 4</li>\r\n			<li>\r\n				Take away kits will be provided to each team. (To know more about the kit, Click on the download course structure)</li>\r\n			<li>\r\n				Competition among teams on the lines of the event in Quark, after the workshop.</li>\r\n			<li>\r\n				Exclusive Session on C programming</li>\r\n			<li>\r\n				A doubt Solving Session and Special Tips and Tricks on conquering Line Following competitions</li>\r\n			<li>\r\n				Certificate to each participant by Graviton and Grey Orange Robotics Click to read more about <a href="http://www.acyut.com/web/webpages/" style="color: inherit;"> Team Acyut</a> or <a href="http://www.greyorangerobotics.com/home.html" style="color: inherit;">Grey Orange Robotics</a></li>\r\n		</ol>\r\n		<p>\r\n			&nbsp;</p>\r\n		<h3 style="padding: 6px;">\r\n			<span style="margin-left: 20px;"><strong>Registrations are closed</strong></span></h3>\r\n	</div>\r\n	<p style="padding: 3px;">\r\n		<strong>For more details contact:</strong><br />\r\n		Laveena Punjabi || +91 9323568577<br />\r\n		laveena@bits-quark.org</p>\r\n</div>\r\n', 'Other', 'graviton', ''),
('4af47bd7-35c8-4c5c-a4b4-1444bb1aea99', 'Workshops', '<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&#39;Following the virtues of Gandhi Ji, an ounce of practice is worth more than tones of preaching, workshops are the impetus of Quark, propelling its success to unobtrusive heights.</p>\r\n<p class="info-box">\r\n	<span style="background-attachment: scroll; background-position: 0% 0%">A gateway for those who are willing to test their acumen in a new field, or gain expertise under abet of the best professionals, the workshops span all spheres of the industrial and the educational world<span style="background: white; color: rgb(34,34,34)">.</span></span></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<strong>Quark 2011</strong> is finally here, all set to deliver workshops that will help you span new horizons and boost your creativity. Here goes the list&hellip;</p>\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<a href="http://www.bits-quark.org/portal/Mu_sigma" target="_self"><strong>Analytics Workshop </strong></a>by<strong> MuSigma<br />\r\n		</strong>Learn the basics of analytics and its potential in business from the leaders in the field<br />\r\n		&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<a href="http://www.bits-quark.org/portal/cypress_workshop" target="_self">PSoC Workshop </a>by <strong>Cypress Semiconductors<br />\r\n		</strong>Cypress Semiconductors, California - presents the PSoC 3/5 programmable system-on-chip architecture that gives you the freedom to imagine revolutionary <br />\r\n		new products.<br />\r\n		&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<a href="http://www.bits-quark.org/portal/social_media">Workshop on Social Media Marketing </a>- by<strong> Digital Vidya</strong><br />\r\n		Explore the power of the latest fad in the marketing world! Become social media experts &amp;&nbsp; enable yourself to earn a roll of bucks! Capitalize on the vogue Addiction! <br />\r\n		&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<a href="http://www.bits-quark.org/portal/cuda_nvidia"><strong>CUDA Workshop</strong></a> by<strong> Nvidia<br />\r\n		</strong>Learn <strong>NVIDIA</strong>&#39;s <strong>parallel computing architecture</strong>. Explore the field of graphics and its applications!<br />\r\n		&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<a href="http://www.bits-quark.org/portal/fuel_cell_greenadd"><strong>Fuel Cell Development </strong></a>by<strong> GreenAdd+</strong><br />\r\n		Discover the Technology that will change the face of global transportation and related issues. Make your own <strong>hydrogen powered car</strong>!<br />\r\n		&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<a href="http://www.bits-quark.org/portal/ornithopter"><strong>Ornithopter Workshop </strong></a>by<strong> AerotriX</strong><br />\r\n		Scale the zeniths or challenge the mighty empyrean for a mano-a-mano with your very own creation... This workshop gives you just the opportunity!!!<br />\r\n		&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<a href="http://www.bits-quark.org/portal/windows_phone_7" target="_self">Development of<strong> Applications on Win7 Phone </strong></a>by<strong> Microsoft<br />\r\n		</strong>Explore the brand new Windows 7 Platform and develop&nbsp;riveting applications on it!<br />\r\n		&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<a href="http://www.bits-quark.org/portal/fractals_workshop" target="_self">Workshop On Fractals </a>- By Dr. Jonathan Wolfe<br />\r\n		Explore the world of<a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fractal"> Fractals </a>with Dr. Jonathan, Executive director, Fractal Foundation, New Mexico. A Must for all&nbsp;Maths&nbsp;and Science enthusiasts! <br />\r\n		&nbsp;</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p>\r\n	<a href="http://www.bits-quark.org/portal/files/Quark_Workshop_Schedule.pdf" target="_blank">Click Here</a> to Download the Workshop Schedule.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<strong><span _fck_bookmark="1" style="display: none">&nbsp;</span><span _fck_bookmark="1" style="display: none">&nbsp;</span><span _fck_bookmark="1" style="display: none">&nbsp;</span><span _fck_bookmark="1" style="display: none">&nbsp;</span><span _fck_bookmark="1" style="display: none">&nbsp;</span><span _fck_bookmark="1" style="display: none">&nbsp;</span><span _fck_bookmark="1" style="display: none">&nbsp;</span><span _fck_bookmark="1" style="display: none">&nbsp;</span></strong></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<br />\r\n	<strong>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <br />\r\n	<br />\r\n	</strong><strong>~</strong> <em><strong>Be curious always! For knowledge will not acquire you: you must acquire it.</strong></em> <strong>~</strong></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<span style="background-color: rgb(255,255,255)">For any query or information, please mail: <strong>workshops@bits-quark.org</strong></span></p>\r\n', 'Other', 'workshops', ''),
('4af47e89-4ad8-4da8-8d41-1444bb1aea99', 'Guest Lectures', '<p>\r\n	<span class="Apple-style-span" style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif">&quot;Education is not the filling of a pail but the lighting of a fire.&quot;<br />\r\n	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; --&nbsp; <strong>William Butler Yeats</strong>&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<div>\r\n	<div>\r\n		<span style="font-size: 12px"><span style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif">&nbsp;</span></span></div>\r\n	<div>\r\n		<span style="font-size: 12px"><span style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif">Igniting minds since the very inception of Quark, the guest lectures give a taste of a world of knowledge and learning which is much beyond what we have already experienced. With enlightening talks by notable speakers, including Nobel Laureates Sir Harry Kroto and Douglas Oshoroff, and Victor Hayes (commonly addressed as the &#39;Father of Wi-Fi&#39;), the guest lectures give us a glimpse and an insight into the world of science and engineering in a way we would never have imagined before.</span></span></div>\r\n	<div>\r\n		&nbsp;</div>\r\n	<div>\r\n		<span class="Apple-style-span" style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif">&quot;When you are inspired by some great purpose, all your thoughts break their bounds, your mind transcends limitations, your consciousness expands in every direction, you find yourself in a new great and wonderful world.&quot;</span></div>\r\n	<div>\r\n		<p style="text-align: right">\r\n			<span style="font-size: 12px"><span style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif">- Ex-President of India, His Excellency <strong>Dr. A.P.J. Abdul Kalam</strong><br />\r\n			quoting Maharishi Patanjali during Quark &#39;09</span></span></p>\r\n		<div>\r\n			&nbsp;</div>\r\n	</div>\r\n	<div>\r\n		&nbsp;</div>\r\n	<div>\r\n		<span class="Apple-style-span" style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif">Quark 2011&nbsp;is here with lectures by&nbsp;inspiring&nbsp;leaders from the realm of Science, Technology, Management &amp; Business who will take you into new horizons of motivation, the resonance of which will leave you spell bound.</span></div>\r\n</div>\r\n<p>\r\n	<span style="font-size: 12px"><span style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif">So be ready with a pen and paper for autographs...</span></span></p>\r\n<div>\r\n	<span style="font-size:14px;"><span class="Apple-style-span" style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; "><strong><a href="http://www.bits-quark.org/portal/jonathan_fractals" target="_self">Fractal Show and Workshop&nbsp;<br />\r\n	</a></strong>by Dr. Jonathan Wolfe,<br />\r\n	Executive Director, Fractal Foundation, New Mexico</span>&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	<span class="Apple-style-span" style="font-size: 14px; "><a href="/portal/isro_lecture"><strong>Satellite Navigation</strong></a></span></div>\r\n<div>\r\n	<span style="font-size:14px;"><span class="Apple-style-span">Mr. Vilas Palsule</span></span></div>\r\n<div>\r\n	<span style="font-size:14px;">ISRO Ahmedabad Director(DECU)</span></div>\r\n<div>\r\n	<div>\r\n		<font class="Apple-style-span" color="#000000" face="arial, sans-serif" size="3"><span class="Apple-style-span" style="border-collapse: collapse; font-size: 13px;"><br />\r\n		</span></font></div>\r\n	<div>\r\n		<span class="Apple-style-span" style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; ">For any query or information, please mail: guestlectures@bits-quark.org</span></div>\r\n</div>\r\n', 'Other', 'guest_lectures', ''),
('4af4a30e-13fc-4660-86a1-1444bb1aea99', 'Contact Us', '<h2 style="text-align: center;">\r\n	<span class="Apple-style-span" style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: 16px;">Postal Address<br />\r\n	<span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><span class="Apple-style-span" style="font-family: Arial,Verdana,sans-serif; font-weight: normal; font-size: 12px;"><strong>Quark Coordination Committee<br />\r\n	<span class="Apple-style-span" style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif; font-weight: normal;">BITS, Pilani || K. K. Birla Goa Campus<br />\r\n	NH - 17B, Zuarinagar, Goa</span></strong></span></span></span> <br />\r\n	<span class="Apple-style-span" style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: 16px;"><span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><span class="Apple-style-span" style="font-family: Arial,Verdana,sans-serif; font-weight: normal; font-size: 12px;"><strong><span class="Apple-style-span" style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif; font-weight: normal;">INDIA - 403726.<br />\r\n	Fax: +91 832 2557031</span></strong></span></span></span></h2>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2>\r\n	Events</h2>\r\n<p>\r\n	<strong>Ritwik Sahoo </strong><br />\r\n	+91 9637423552<br />\r\n	ritwik@bits-<span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;">quark.</span>org</p>\r\n<h2 style="text-align: right;">\r\n	Reception &amp; Accommodation</h2>\r\n<p style="text-align: right;">\r\n	<strong>R.S.S Harsha</strong><br />\r\n	+91 9676658505&nbsp; <br />\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2>\r\n	Workshops &amp; Guest Lectures</h2>\r\n<p>\r\n	<strong>Arpit Goyal</strong><br />\r\n	+91 9503817729<br />\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2 style="text-align: right;">\r\n	Sponsorship &amp; Marketing</h2>\r\n<p style="text-align: right;">\r\n	<strong>Advait Tinaikar</strong><br />\r\n	+91 9673995192 <br />\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2>\r\n	Publicity &amp; Public Relations</h2>\r\n<p>\r\n	<strong>Shreyans Jain</strong><br />\r\n	+91 9637423567</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2 style="text-align: right;">\r\n	Aurora &amp; Exhibitions</h2>\r\n<p style="text-align: right;">\r\n	<strong>Rahul Choudhury<br />\r\n	+91 8298158653</strong> <br />\r\n	<br />\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2>\r\n	Asset Coordinator</h2>\r\n<p>\r\n	<strong>Tanmaya Sanghvi</strong><br />\r\n	+91 <span dir="ltr" id=":1mz">9922461628<br />\r\n	</span> tanmaya@bits-quark.org<span dir="ltr" id=":1mz"><br />\r\n	</span></p>\r\n<h2 style="text-align: center;">\r\n	Convener</h2>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;">\r\n	<strong>Pranay Agrawal<br />\r\n	</strong>+91 9637423510<br />\r\n	pranay@bits-quark.org<br />\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;">\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;">\r\n	<span style="color: rgb(128, 128, 128);"><span style="font-size: 16px;"><strong>Council for Student Affairs<br />\r\n	</strong></span></span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;">\r\n	<strong>Manoj Malineni | President</strong><br />\r\n	+91 9422311111<br />\r\n	prez@bits-goa.ac.in</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;">\r\n	<strong>Habbu Shreyas | Vice-President</strong><br />\r\n	+91 9552101319<br />\r\n	viceprez@bitsgoa.ac.in</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;">\r\n	<strong>&nbsp;Akshit Rao | Treasurer</strong><br />\r\n	+91 9561713838<br />\r\n	trez@bits-goa.ac.in</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;">\r\n	<strong>Kushal Khandelwal | General Secretary</strong><br />\r\n	+91 9637423510<br />\r\n	gensec@bits-goa.ac.in</p>\r\n', 'Other', 'contact_us', ''),
('4af8e286-94fc-4763-9c71-1064bb1aea99', 'Exhibitions', '<p>\r\n	<span style="font-size: 12px;">The true display of technical talent and scientific research, now on display for the viewing pleasure of the more technically inclined public, the exhibitions feature some of the most exciting and cutting edge work that is currently being done in the world of science and engineering. Previous participating organizations have included the likes of the <strong>Defence Research and Development Organization</strong> (<strong>DRDO</strong>), the <strong>Council of Scientific and Industrial Research</strong> (<strong>CSIR</strong>) and <strong>India Space Research Organization</strong> (<strong>ISRO</strong>), and the coming days only promise to be bigger and better.</span></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<span style="font-size: 12px;"><span class="Apple-style-span" style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: arial,sans-serif; border-collapse: collapse;">At Quark 2011 , witness the power of touch, the ability to lend life to an entire wall with insignificant movement of your hands. <a href="http://www.touchmagix.com/">TouchMagix</a> brings to you this exclusively electrifying, free-of-cost experience that will form the silver lining of the cloud called Quark, the annual techno-managerial festival of BITS-Pilani, K.K. Birla Goa Campus. Play sports virtually on screen with your own feet, splash colours of your emotions and toy around frolicsome touch-sensitive walls letting the efficacy of technology manifest your moods. Observe the majestic, labyrinthine electronic screens as they sense the dynamics of your feet and form congruous projections of the football, pulling out all the stops in teleporting you to the realms of fantasies.</span></span></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Quark&rsquo;s Technology Lounge introduces you to this fascinating arena constituted of nothing, but the ultimate gaming experience. Equipped with the latest, hi-tech gaming technology like X-Box 360, PS2 and PS3, this lounge is a perfect island to harbor your addiction to gaming.<br />\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Another major attraction in Quark 2011 is&nbsp; <strong>Metalmate&#39;s Exhibition Robots and Robosoccer</strong>.Watch the Robots from Metalmate do tricks and shows that will simply amaze you. A soccer robot is a specialized autonomous robot and mobile robot that is used to play variants of soccer. This Quark come with your friends take the control in your hand and play 1 v 1 soccer with these robots . Visit <a href="http://www.bits-quark.org/portal/metalmate_exhibitions">this page</a> for more details. </p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<span style="font-family: courier new,monospace;"><br />\r\n	<br />\r\n	</span></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<span style="font-size: 12px;"><br />\r\n	<br />\r\n	</span></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	For any query or information, please mail: <strong>exhibitions@bits-quark.org</strong></p>\r\n', 'Other', 'exhibitions', '');
