arial, helvetica, sans-serif; ">Bio of Dr.Nikolaos Mavridis&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;</span></strong></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-align: justify; ">\r\n	<span lang="EN-US"><span class="Apple-style-span" style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; "><a href="http://www.dr-nikolaos-mavridis.com/">Dr.Nikolaos Mavridis</a> has received his PhD from the Massachusetts Institute of Technology (MIT) Media Lab in 2007, after receiving his MSEE from UCLA and a MEng in ECE from the Aristotle University of Thessaloniki. Currently, he is serving as an Assistant Professor at the College of IT of the United Arab Emirates University, where he has founded the Interactive Robots and Media Laboratory (IRML). The lab is home to the microsoft-award winning &quot;FaceBots&quot; social robots project, as well as to &quot;IbnSina&quot;, the first arabic-speaking humanlike humanoid. The current research Interests of Dr. Mavridis include: Interactive and Social Robots, Robots and Language, and Cognitive Systems.</span></span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-align: justify; ">\r\n	For more details and videos visit <a href="http://alumni.media.mit.edu/~nmav/index.htm">http://alumni.media.mit.edu/~nmav/index.htm</a></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-align: justify; line-height: normal;">\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-align: justify; line-height: normal;">\r\n	<span class="Apple-style-span" style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; border-collapse: collapse; "><u><strong>Sand Animation</strong></u></span></p>\r\n<div>\r\n	<span class="Apple-style-span" style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; border-collapse: collapse; "><br />\r\n	</span></div>\r\n<div>\r\n	<span class="Apple-style-span" style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; border-collapse: collapse; ">Sand Animation is a fairly recent and unconventional form of stage performance. An artist tells a story by drawing&nbsp;pictures using sand as an unusual medium on a backlighted glass table. Images overlap to form new ones, and&nbsp;build a gripping tale through shades and layers of sand which give way to the seemingly fluid light underneath, &nbsp;accompanied by equally gripping music.&nbsp;It is truly an enriching Aurora of light and sound. The Sand Animation&nbsp;for Quark 2011 is conceptualised and performed by <a href="mailto:kaushalsapre@gmail.com">Kaushal Sapre.</a>&nbsp;, a BITSian .&nbsp;</span></div>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-align: justify; line-height: normal;">\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-align: justify; line-height: normal;">\r\n	<span style="font-family:arial, helvetica, sans-serif;"><span style="font-size:12px;"><strong>The Fractals Show</strong>&nbsp;</span></span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-align: justify; line-height: normal;">\r\n	<span style="font-family:arial, helvetica, sans-serif;"><span style="font-size:12px;">Another major highlight of the Quark Special Nights would be <a href="http://www.bits-quark.org/portal/jonathan_fractals">The Fractals Show </a><span class="Apple-style-span">by <a href="http://fractalfoundation.org/about-us/jonathan-wolfe/">Dr. Jonathan Wolfe</a>,&nbsp;</span><span class="Apple-style-span">Executive Director, Fractal Foundation, New Mexico . Fractals are interesting Geometric shapes which have a special property known as &quot;self - similarity&quot; . They have applications in all fields ranging from Computer gaming and Design and Image compression to Fracture Mechanics ,Seismology and Generation of New Music .</span></span></span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-align: justify; line-height: normal;">\r\n	<span style="font-family:arial, helvetica, sans-serif;"><span style="font-size:12px;"><span class="Apple-style-span">To know more about Fractals and the Fractal Foundation visit&nbsp;</span><a href="http://fractalfoundation.org/">http://fractalfoundation.org/</a></span></span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-align: justify; line-height: normal;">\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-align: justify; line-height: normal;">\r\n	<strong>The AerotriX Show</strong>&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-align: justify; line-height: normal;">\r\n	<span style="font-size:12px;"><span style="font-family:arial, helvetica, sans-serif;">I<span class="Apple-style-span" style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); line-height: 16px; ">f you get excited just by watching F1 races or by playing NFS, get ready to face the action in the real world. Here are the expert flyers of <a href="http://www.aerotrix.com/">AerotriX</a> coming with their extreme machines just to take you into a world of speed and thrill. Feel the power of extreme engineering and flying skills as the plane flies past you taking you into your closest encounters with thrill.</span></span></span></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<span _fck_bookmark="1" style="display: none; ">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-align: justify; line-height: normal;">\r\n	<span style="font-family:arial, helvetica, sans-serif;"><span style="font-size