('4afb5626-0cdc-4707-9a93-10640a040761', 'BITSMUN', '<h2>\r\n	Introduction</h2>\r\n<p>\r\n	A Model United Nations conference simulates the real world working of the United Nations Organizations. Through it, we hope to provide the youth of today a chance to discuss global issues and come up with solutions that could change the world in the long run</p>\r\n<h2>\r\n	Event Specifications</h2>\r\n<h3>\r\n	Structure of BITSMUN 2011</h3>\r\n<h4>\r\n	The General Assembly</h4>\r\n<p>\r\n	The General Assembly will discuss overall policy matters. It aims at giving developing nations an equal voice on the international stage.</p>\r\n<h4>\r\n	The Security Council</h4>\r\n<p>\r\n	The Security Council will debate strategic issues, with focus on international threats of terrorism, nuclear proliferation and territorial disputes.</p>\r\n<h4>\r\n	The Economic and Social Council</h4>\r\n<p>\r\n	The Economic and Social Council will discuss economic policy matters, focussing on international trade and greater synergy between the economies of the world.</p>\r\n<h4>\r\n	The Press Corps</h4>\r\n<p>\r\n	BITSMUN will also consist of a Press Corps which will conduct press conferences, report council progress and publish council-related newsletters for circulation amongst delegates.</p>\r\n<h3>\r\n	&nbsp;Agenda</h3>\r\n<h4>\r\n	General Assembly</h4>\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Formulating a global framework for the management of transnational resources.</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Developing an effective and just roadmap for the control of carbon emissions in order to combat climate change.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p>\r\n	Suggested Reading: Ensuring the sustainable development of mega-cities.</p>\r\n<h4>\r\n	Security Council</h4>\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Evolving a comprehensive plan to minimise the impact of war material after cessation of hostilities.</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Preventing the destruction during war of strategic targets that would result in a large-scale environmental disaster.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p>\r\n	Suggested Reading: Exploring possible changes to make the existing nuclear proliferation regulations fairer and more effective.</p>\r\n<h4>\r\n	Economic and Social Council</h4>\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Addressing concerns of food security over the use of food crops as bio-fuel.</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Developing a robust mechanism for the transfer of low-carbon technology to the developing world.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<h2>\r\n	Rules of Procedure</h2>\r\n<p>\r\n	The rules of procedure will be uploaded soon.</p>\r\n<h2>\r\n	Resources</h2>\r\n<p>\r\n	The study guide will be uploaded soon.</p>\r\n<h2>\r\n	Eligibility</h2>\r\n<p>\r\n	Participants should be bonafide students of any educational institution, studying in grade XI or above. (Post-graduate students are also allowed to participate.)</p>\r\n<h2>\r\n	Certification Policy</h2>\r\n<p>\r\n	Certificate of participation will be awarded to all delegates.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Certificate of merit will be awarded to outstanding delegates.</p>\r\n<h2>\r\n	Links</h2>\r\n<p>\r\n	BITSMUN 2011 Official Blog: <a href="http://www.bits-quark.org/bitsmunblog">http://www.bits-quark.org/bitsmunblog</a></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Follow Us on Twitter: <a href="http://www.twitter.com/bitsmun">http://www.twitter.com/bitsmun</a></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Facebook: <a href="http://www.facebook.com/bitsmun">http://www.facebook.com/bitsmun</a></p>\r\n<h2>\r\n	Contact Us</h2>\r\n<p>\r\n	<strong>Email address - bitsmun@bits-quark.org</strong></p>\r\n', 'Other', 'bitsmun', ''),
